\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid4284859 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Can you tell me where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I was born in Sneinton. But I can't tell you exactly 
the number and I can't tell you exactly the - the street. I think it was Storey Street, so they tell me but I can't remember that. Down Nenton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you know how many years you lived in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What, down at Sneinton, oh only - only a few - fe
w because I come here when I were - come to Daybrook when I were three, so - and I know we didn't live there very long. But I come to Daybrook when I were three years old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Where did you live when you were in Daybrook, Sherbrook Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 That - first house at - on that side, up there. Miss Roses lives there now, I don't know whether you know her, she goes to church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How many years did you live in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 That house, well not long because we went higher up street and I were brought up -
 from about five years old I was - brought up in a house as stood by itself. It was top of - top of Sherbrook Road, there were only three houses up there then and ours was one, and then there was two more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you spend most of your childhood in that house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Could you tell me how many brothers and sisters you had, starting with the oldest and working down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well the oldest - I'm the oldest. My name was William. Then there was me brother John. Me brother, and me brothe
r Fred. And me sister May. And me sister Annie. Well Annie and May's alive but the brothers has died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 We were going to work out how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well, me father - I couldn't tell you how - I don't know - I were thirteen when - when he died and - he was - in his fortieth year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Where did he come from?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 He were born in - he were a Nottingham man. But I don't know where he were born, he was born in Nottingham, that's all - me mother as well.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you know what his job was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 He was in same - he were - he were in the dying - dying department in the - lace trade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did he have a special title for his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, no, just ordinary work - working man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did he have any other jobs before or after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No. That all his life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did he ever tell you how old he was when he started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, I should think he'd be about the same - about thirteen, as I - as far as I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did he have any casual or part time jobs as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you ever remember him being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Where did your mother come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 She come from - off of St Ansell Road in Nottingham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did she have any jobs before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes, she was in - she wa
s in the - lace trade but - I don't know what she did, I couldn't tell you what she did, she - but that's what she was in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did she work after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did she do any work at home after she was married, did she draw lace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 She - yes, she used to draw lace, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 So she could look after the children herself?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
That's right. They did - there weren't many women as went out to work, they had it - work they did was at home. Seaming and drawing lace and clipping and scalloping and all like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How many rooms were there in the house you went to when you were five?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 When we went up there, there was - a rather biggish house, it was six shilling a week and - there was a bathroom - upstairs. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Scullery, kitchen and front room and a - and a - a nice front passage. Two bedrooms and an attic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was it a new house when you went in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You said you had a bathroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes, well - well - aye, it was it was six shilling a week, well - it was - 'c
ourse six shilling then were a lot of money. Majority - these houses when I first came in there was four and threepence. How they're one pound one and - about one pound one and so many pence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did anyone else besides your parents and brother and sisters live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well - we had a brother - well I forgot to mention him but he - he was - he was me half brother, lived with us. He was me dad's - son, but not me mother's. Well he lived with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was he a lot older than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes, he'd 
be ten years older than me. He was me father's lad but - before he married me mother. He'd - his mother died while - in his - while he were infant. He never knew her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your mother have any help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was the washing done at home or sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Done at home. You couldn't afford to send it out, we used to take somebody else's in as well. Me mother did. Oh aye, she had to do. 'Cos we were left with no father - father was and she - she got this - see after 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 So she didn't take washing in while your father was alive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh no. No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your father or mother make or mend the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Me father used to make our - suits when we were little. Father. Yes, he was - he - he went - he learnt tailoring in his - at night. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 
He learnt it at night somewhere, I don't know where, I can't remember, but he'd learn it and - and he used to - I tell you what he used to do and all - if anyone wanted a - bottom of their trousers turning up, he were proficient at it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Aye, could turn peoples' trousers up and you couldn't tell from what they'd come from the tailor - well he was a - he - he'd learnt the trade. But he never - never followed it up, he always worked across here.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your mother do anything about making clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh she used to make }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 children\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  frocks and all like that when - mend and all like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Apart from the ones the family made were the clothes new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh they were new, what we had, when we - when we were rigged out every Whitsuntide we always used to have a new suit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Every Whitsun?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 About every Whitsun, yes, new suits and new boots. The girls used to have - new dresses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were your boots always new?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes. Oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When were they bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh - anywhere where they were cheapest. Can't tell you exactly, mostly in Nottingham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You sued to go to Nottingham to shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes. Mostly, yes. Well there weren't many shops here then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Would your new clothes have been bought in Nottingham?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your father help your mother with any jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Not many.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did he do any that you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh he might - might have cleaned the windows or some jobs like that or - he had a garden, he used to - be mostly in the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Would he have helped with the cooking or washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Helped? No. Not as I know of, I can't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Would he have helped with the fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Fires. Oh fetch coal in, well it was cellar. Fetch coal in and - or chop some sticks and jobs like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Decorating or repairs or improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, no decorating. No. Didn't do none of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did he dress or undress you when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well he used to help, if it were a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 bath night}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 So he did bath you too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Sometimes, aye. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did he read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh some - occasionally like. Read us - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 children\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did he tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh aye, used to tell us some stories.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you remember any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did he take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Oh he used to take us out. Me - me and me brother - me - me brother - me youngest brother and he was only a baby then, like we - we were only small. He used to take us seaside for half day and again and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did he look after you while your mother was out?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh we were - we were never left - we were never left in the house with ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have any tasks you had to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 carry}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  out regularly at home to help your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I used to r
un all errands when I used to go to Nottingham fetch - used to go to Nottingham and fetch groceries, I did, very often. 'Cos - in Nottingham it was cheaper, there used to be a shop - well it's still there now - Burtons on - on the - on the Exchange.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 That was cheap then was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 That - aye, cheap - cheaper than what - was - was in Arnold.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I always think of it as an expensive shop now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well it - it is - it's - 'cos it's high class shop and they put - put it on a bit. But years ago when it
 was a small shop Burtons - you - you used to - most people used to go there because you could get things - much cheaper than what you could from these little corner shops. And I used to go on Saturday morning - and fetch - mother's bacon, butter and lard
, sugar. All them sort of things. Used to go on bus. Used to be threeha'pence on the bus. Threeha'pence ride.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was this a horse bus?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Where did it start from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Started from up Arnold, agen the Robin Hood. Just a bit lower down than your - your place. Robin Hood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 And it took you all the way for threeha'pence?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Aye, it took us down - to Columbus Street, threeha'pence. Well it were only tuppence for - adult.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were there any jobs in the house you did to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I used to
 - used to help like mother - going errands and doing little bits of jobs she ask me to do, but I - can't remember what like particular. Anything that she asked me to do we used to do. But I weren't - I weren't very old, were only thirteen when he died so
 I couldn't do -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you remember what jobs your sisters had to help in the home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
They just - helped to wash up and like that. Same as I say, when me father died - I were only thirteen, I were the oldest, and they went down - went down form about
 four years between us. Three and four years. So the youngest only be a - she were - well she didn't - never knowed father. The youngest sister. Only a baby. Weren't very old. She were - I don't think - don't think she were a year old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did the older children help the younger with things they found difficult?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I used to - we would - company for one another, just help one an other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did the younger children help the older in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - I don't know - I can't remember they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh aye, we went to bed early.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you know what time it was, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh - summertime used to be a bit later than wintertime. Round about half}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9196494\charrsid6628200 
 past seven to eight}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  - then of course when we got older we used to go a bit - later.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, after me - after me father - she used to put the youngest to bed me mother did but - me and me brothers, we used to - I used to take
 them too, the two and - we all went - all three went together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When you were very little your mother put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh yes. Oh aye, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you remember what age you started putting yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well I was - that's - perhaps nine years of age, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you share a bedroom or a bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Me and - another brother, then - together, then one of me brothers were in - one of his own, a little bed of his own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Where were the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 They were in - them two were in a bed of their own.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was this in the same room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well, the girls was in the same room as me mother. See when me father died we had to shift around a bit you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Where were they before then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - I can't tell you, I can't - I can't ever remember now. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You said you actually had a bathroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 We did up there, but - we - we were left from up there - left from up there and went in - in a house in another part.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How often did you bath when you had a bathroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh I used to have some - when it was hot weather like this you used to be - dropping in the bath every day - every night rather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How did they heat the water for the bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well heat it from the back fire boiler.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When did you put clean clothes on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Clean clothes? Oh every - once a week we had clean clothes and that - that - only once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was this any special day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well it used to be Friday night as a rule.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 So you had to keep clean on Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Aye, that's right. Friday night. That were bath night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 All had them in kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were there any occasions when they ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Where did your mother cook?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Used to cook in - back kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What did she cook on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Why - I don't think there were any stove - I don't remember any stoves then. Like there is now. I think we used to have a gas ring. Used to get the - gas rings with a rubber pipe to you know in them days. But - sh
e'd got - big range in the - in the kitchen as - like might be this - there a big range with a big oven. They were bigger evens than what they are - what they are today. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did she use that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 So she had both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - as soon - as soon as we could have it before nine o'clock, so we could go to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 There wasn't any special time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. It all depends what time we got up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Who was present for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well the - all them as could sit at table. But - same as I say, me youngest sister, she were only baby so she didn't sit at table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Where did she sit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 She used to sit in a cradle. Mother used to feed her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was your father present at this breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, he were at work then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 So what did he do about his first meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
He - well, him and mother was up first and then - mother used to get his breakfast ready and he'd gone to work before sometimes before we got up because he - had to be there be - for eight o'clock.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What did you usually}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200  eat}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  and drink at breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Oh used to have a - reasonable, sometimes it - tea - tea and - either toast and - sometimes if we got a bit of bacon if were a bit well off we used to have a bit of bac
on and - Sunday we used to have egg. Egg and bacon. Or egg - boiled egg, but only on a Sunday. Didn't get no eggs on - in the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What about midday meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh we used to have proper dinners. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What sort of things would you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well - leg of beef stewed and - broth in winter, pea soup. Tatoe - potato and meat pie and - and all them sort of things. Sometimes boiled fish. Parsley sauce. 'Course we'd got a big garden back of the - house as we lived up there and we used to grow all
 us own vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have anything different to eat on Sundays in the middle of the day, was it a special day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, we used to have drop of roast - piece of roast beef - Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What was the next meal of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What would that have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - mother used to make some - scones in the oven, bake them herself. That's - perhaps a jam tart, big jam tart. Something like that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Would that have been different on a Sunday in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh we used to have a - we used to have a good dinner every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Anything after that or before going to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well we used to have some - perhaps have some - bread and jam or something like that, we didn't have no - no - particular - us young 'uns didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your mother or father bake bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Mother used to bake sometimes. Not all - not regular, she'd bake - she would - fancy making a bit of homemade bread she used to make it.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did she make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Jam? Oh aye, she made jam 'cos I've heard her - we used
 to have a lot of black - currants trees and apple trees up - when we lived up there. Oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did she bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No. Never bottle any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did she make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 She made pickled onions, pickled cabbage. Me dad used to
 grow cabbage and - and onions, so we used to have plenty of them. Used to have 'em in big jars them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did she make wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did she make any medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Only the old fashioned - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 chamomiles}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  and - used to have them and - rue and - dad used to grow rue and wormwood and all them sort of herbs. Used to grow 'em and dry 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you remember what they were used for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - wormwood made so you could eat. Used to make us eat and - aye. Clear your stomach.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What was rue?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
That was - that - we used to have rue and all. Rue - rue were mixed with wormwood and - were nasty but - I can remember it. And then we used to have some - now what - brimstone and treacle, we used to have that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have this regularly or just sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, no, only when we didn't feel very well we used to - we used to get this brimstone and treacle and - we all had to have it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was any beer brewed for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh yes, mother used to make herb beer. Used to gather }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 herbs}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  from off of - out of fields.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What special herbs did you use?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh - I can't tell you the names, there's all sorts. Dandelions and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 \endash }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 foalafoot.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
. And - oh - about three more I think, I can't remember now - what name of them was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 It was good beer was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh it were - it was and all. Used to go to the brewery and fetch a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 
penn'orth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  of balm, used to get a - quart jugful for a penny. Used to make - mother made beer every week. Used to make it in little stone bottles. You don't see }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 none}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  - 
earthenware they was, you don't see - see many about now. Never seen 'em for years. Oh aye, mother made beer every week in summer. Well sometimes in winter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You say they grew vegetables and fruit, did you provide enough or did she ever buy any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
What fruit? Sometimes, in winter - when - it would eat up. We used to grow a nice lot of potatoes and - and all them sort of things. Celery and them kind - grow celery and - radish or onions and all like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you ever have tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Used to have prunes, dried prunes. That were all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your mother have any feelings about tinned foods?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well there weren't - there were only tomatoes then - there weren't - weren't tinned fruit as there is now, there were onl
y about tomatoes. That's about all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did they keep any livestock for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 We used to keep a few fowls, bottom of the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Who looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh dad used to see to them. Mother used to feed them sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well when we didn't have fish every - every time - every day, barring - barring fish day. Every day, some sort of meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you ever have tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Tinned? No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you ever get any extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh used to have rabbits. Oh aye, we got some rabbits. Used to get a rabbit then for ninepence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Where did these come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh I don't know. We didn't care much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How often did you get a rabbit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh sometimes we had one every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 But you didn't ask questions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. Used to go to door, do you want a rabbit? Ask mother, say, do you want a rabbit? How much is it? Ninepence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you remember seeing your mother having less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 She did when me father was died. Aye, she often went without when me father died. I know that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When your father was alive did he have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, don't know, no, I think he only had his share and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were you allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Oh - they weren't on that strict on us as - you know - talk to one another if you - wanted to know anything, like ask a question or anything like that, but - we didn't used to have no conversations like while we were eating. Much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 We used to have what were cooked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What was your parents attitude if you left some food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 We never left none.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What would have happened if you did, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well, now - I don't think me parents was - they weren't as strict as all that because - if there were any left as I say we used to keep a few fowls and they had it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 If there was something on the table you wanted, like salt, could you ask someone to pass it to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh yes. Aye, oh yes, used to - used to have to be - bit reserved in that respect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You couldn't ask, you had to wait?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 We used to ask for - if we wanted any salt or pepper or anything like that, or mustard or whatever it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You could if there were enough. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way or sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh well - oh learnt how to - how to eat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Could you bring toys or books to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - as a rule mostly about all finished together then we used to all - get up then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Would you have had to wait 'til the end if you'd finished first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No. No, we weren't - weren't - got any parents like that as were that strict. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did all the family sit at the table for a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh yes. Oh yes. They all sat at table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you always have the same places at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How was the meal served?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Mother used to serve it out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What order were you served in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - father - his dinner was first and then - mother used to go round according to us age and how - how
 much we wanted, she knew how much each - each could eat and she used to start at them as wanted the most, she used to work round to them that wanted least.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 So was it sort of oldest first usually or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, because - it always took them longer to eat it more or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 The baby was fed in the cradle, not on somebodys' knee or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I think - I think me mother - breast fed it, 'til she were - weaned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What would happen then, did you have high chairs or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh aye, she had high chair, young 'un did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Would she have sat at the table with you when she was in her high chair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 She - when she was old enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh aye, she were - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did she show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 My mother? My word she did. She looked after us when me father died and - she had a struggle but - she stuck it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 If you had any worries could you share them with her or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well she - she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 kept}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  a lot from us, she didn't tell 
us anything, and she were - she - you know, she bore it - because we were so young, she bore it - most of it herself. I - I had the - I had - the most - anxiety for me mother, I - it were me as - had it. I was the oldest you see. I - I knew - I understood
 but it - the others didn't understand do you see, they didn't know. But I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 If you had worries when you were little could you share them with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What about your father, was he easy to talk to?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did he show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 If you had any worries could you share them with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 him}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - used to have to do as you were told and - if we didn't we - we - got some 
strap. Well, strap - me mother used to have a cane. And we - we had to do as we were told.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you get the cane very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. We did when we did - anything was - as we didn't ought to do and - and they told us not to do it and we did do it and
 then we used to catch it. But not - not very often. We didn't - we - we didn't get knocked - knocked about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you ever get the strap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh aye. Oh aye, we were very - close to one another in - that respect. Me brothers and sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Mr Browning could answer to the question, what kind of people do yo
u think your parents hoped you'd to be, etc. He said he didn't come across swearing in the home and they would have caught it if they had been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When grown up were talking, if it was important they were not allowed to join in, otherwise they were. If 
they did something their parents approved of they would have got the strap, more from the mother than from father, but not very often in any case. The mother would also use a cane. Again mother more than father, but only occasionally. He did give a very i
nteresting instance of getting a good thrashing after having played }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 truant}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
 from school, I will try to get this on tape again, He said both parents played an equal part in bringing up the children. Birthdays were very little different from any other day, the
y night have had a tea party with a few buns, ginger beer and a few friends in. He can't remember getting any birthday presents. \{BLANK\} Christmas he called a Dickensian Christmas. Said it was jolly, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 decorating}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  up, cousins came, extra food, beef and Christ
mas stockings. No musical instruments in the home, the mother occasionally sang. They occasionally joined in carols but that was all. Their parents might have played blind man}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 \rquote }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 s buff with them. There were few books in the house. Newspapers, probably the Po
st, Nottingham Evening Post that is, and Sunday papers. Occasionally magazines. He did remember his parents reading and he did remember them reading aloud. The funeral he remembered in the family was his father's. All the family went but not the baby. And
 
he did wear mourning clothes, as did the others for two or three months. He used to visit a relations, and uncle particularly, going on his own. Father took him out shopping for boots once a year. He also went with his father to the seaside occasionally o
n day trips, and to the sports at Trent Bridge. They also had brake parties to Edwinstowe in the Dukeries. And Bank Holidays no special but he does remember fairs. He }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 only}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  once went away on holiday. He went to an uncle in Lincolnshire for two weeks. Where t
hey were in the country. Saturdays he said weren't very different. He described a little how he spent his pocket money here but I will got that again.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Can you tell me about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well not much, only we used to go to Sunday school and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How many times did you used to go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh we used to go - used to have to go twice. Sunday school twice - on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Morning and afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 That - that - well - when we were all like well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you go to church in the evenings well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No. Didn't go no - not after tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have different clothes on Sunday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh aye, always }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 Sunday}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  best clothes. Yes - Sunday clothes, used to save them for Sundays. Mind you, the week with - used to have one or two patches 
in us clothes because we - me mother - couldn't afford to buy new britches - well you called 'em britches then and - I - I were the oldest and I used to - when I'd done out of mine I used to pass 'em on to me next brother and so on, and that's how - went 
on with sisters as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You probably came off best then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh aye, aye. I used to - I used to get new ones and then when I - grown out of them used to pass them on to me next - lower down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were your Sunday clothes turned into weekday clothes later on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes. I used to be rigged out every Easter - if - used to reckon - mother used to always say, always Sunday clothes for Easter. Yes, oh aye.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you play games on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Games? No, never see'd anybody play games on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your parents think it wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Never - never allowed us to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What were you allowed to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - just the ordinary things, I mean, they weren't what you call extra strict on us but - we used to have to do as
 we were told I know, no playing on Sunday anyway, only - just play with one another in - perhaps in the house or anything like that. But we never used to go out to play, same as a - they do now, football and all that sort of thing, were none of that then
 - in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your parents think it wrong to work on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Never did work, no, they didn't - no, - they wouldn't let you do nothing on a Sunday, only - mother used to cook of course, that was all.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your parents attend a place of worship or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. They didn't either - neither.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Where did you go, which denomination was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I used to go to church - a church Sunday school. St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 Paul\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 . I were in Bible class 'til I was about twenty-two. Yes. And that used to be held at 
the - Daybrook school as it is now. There were about - there'd be about thirty of us all together, well - the vicar used to come and we used to have a - Sunday afternoon Bible class and then - every year - we used to go to - to Charles Sealey's house on t
h
e Mansfield Road you know as is now the - coal board establishment. We used to go there every year and - do you know what we had for us tea? Rabbit pies. Aye. Always rabbit pies and used to bring 'em on - so many on each table. Used to be about thirty of 
u
s go and - when we'd had us tea we used to go on the - grounds you know and - play - ball and one thing and another, cricket and so on and then - used to bring us a - ginger beer and all them kind of things, after tea and - cake. Well that were our - that
 were our annual outing from the - Sunday afternoon class.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you ever have any other Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No, I don't remember any anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What other social activities organised by the church did you take part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, no, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did the church run any temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Not as I know of, I can't remember any. They may have done but I can't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you belong to any other club organised by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Who said it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Why as a rule me mother used to say it. Just a few words you know and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes, always. Friday nights }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 bath night}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
, and we used to have a - cup of cocoa and some - biscuits, me mother used to buy biscuits - we used to like called butter biscuits, a lot of - made of butter. Butter and flour and so on, and we used to - that - that were after we'd been bathed Friday
 night, that were bath night Friday night, then we used to have this cocoa and biscuits, then - upstairs. Bed. That was regular that was, every week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, not as I know of, no. No were not one - there weren't - 
that strict like in religion, I mean - we - we used to - have a - prayer at - thanks giving and - different things as happened and all like that but - we didn't have no - regular prayer as you might say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. He didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you know what his views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
My father used to - used to - take interest in sport, running - running, not - I don't mean horse racing, I mean - sports, there used to be held in Nottingham, used to be twice a year in Notti
ngham at that time of day. Used to be the Forest sports and then there were one - I don't know the - the name of the other but there was two. Well - when I were a lad and me brother were a lad, I were - of course about three or four years older than him, 
a
nd we used to run and me father used to - see after us. We used to do - every year we - well we've been to Leicester and all round, there - used to be a lot of sports in them days and - they don't seem to have 'em now, only the fetes and - used to have sp
orts, and we used to run in 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were you specially good at running?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you win?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh I won two or three prizes but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How seriously was this taken, did you sort of train?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh yes, it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 serious}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 . Very serious. My father was very keen on that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Had he been good in his day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
He had, yes. Yes, he was - he was - used to do it - when he was young and - so it - got - tried to make us same and he passed it onto us and - he used to see after us, oh he would - used to ha
ve a bit extra - to eat when - you know, when that was on, eggs and all like that was - buy us different things to - get us in good form as you might say.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you do other things like jumping or hurdling or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No, we was - only on - when you get one or two - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 pals}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
, and we used to go down on - in - down Valley Road there, we used to go down there, we used to - regular with perhaps five or six of us, well - used to do a bit of running down there and jumping and all that kind of thing. 'C
ourse it were all country then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You say your father didn't take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you know anything at all about his political views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I know he were a Conservative and that's all I know, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you know why he was a Conservative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you know what your mother's views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well my - mother followed me father of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You think this was the custom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 That's it. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you remember either of your parents voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Oh they used to vote every year. Mind you there were only Conservatives and - and Liberals then. There were no Labour. Weren't such a thing as Labour party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 In some places at that time men felt they risked losing
 their jobs or their house if they voted differently from their employers, do you know if your father felt himself under that kind of pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh no, no, I don't think - I don't think his firm took that - interest in what they voted for, I don't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you come across any employers taking that attitude?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I've heard - I've heard of it but I - I couldn't name any - any people as did it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was your father actually a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 And he didn't work for a party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Nor your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did either of them take any part in political activities other than election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No. Just - went to vote and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time, your father was keen on sport, what else was he keen on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well he were keen on boxing. But not the box - not the - what - as it is now, it used to - it were a regular thing then, used to - have a boxing match in - all in good faith you know, it was all - done for fun and - they didn't do it like they do now.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 And he did a lot of gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh aye, he had a - a nice garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. Only to be seeing after us. She'd got enough on I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 She went out to - had - perhaps had a - when there were a party anywhere she used to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did she ever go by herself or was it always with the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, she didn't go - she didn't go by herself anywhere particular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When did your father get home from work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well usually about half past five time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How many evenings would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 He spent about all of them. Most of them. My - might have a walk 
somewhere just for an hour but - that - I don't remember him ever - going away for very long no night. Sundays he didn't go out nowhere, only - at home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did he ever attend any clubs or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I don't know-, he might have gone and had one somewhere, and had a - drink -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you know if he went regularly or just sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well he went - when he got money because he hadn't always got money. I mean - money were - were chief thing them in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your mother go too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Would she have been shocked at the idea or was it the money do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well - women? I never - I don't remember seeing any women going in pubs. In fact there's one - there's - there's a - there's a pub at bottom of street as what when - one land
lord kept it he wouldn't - he wouldn't let women - wouldn't have a woman in. No. Wouldn't have a woman in. Never seen - they might go in with a jug or bottle take - to fetch it out, but they - they didn't go in to sit down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 He would turn them out would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well he wouldn't - he wouldn't have served them. So then they'd have to go out, he - they weren't exactly turned out but it were as good. He wouldn't serve her. Well they hadn't got the money tell you the truth then, they hadn't got the - the p
eople hadn't got the money, they couldn't do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your father attend races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What - horserace? No. No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did he disapprove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, he didn't - he didn't disapprove and he - but he didn't go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did he bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, because they hadn't got none - no - no money to save.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did they belong to any burial clubs or sick clubs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 They were insured, that was all. Oh they used to have the Medical Aid. I know Doc
tor Stenhouse as lived - where you do - many years ago, he used to have a threeha'penny a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Can you tell me more about this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Doctor Stenhouse? Well he used to - man used to come - man named Holbrook used to come round and collect it every we
ek. I don't know whether it were - threeha'pence per head or whether it were threeha'pence for - so many, but it - I know me mother used to pay threeha'pence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 That covered you for free medical aid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you get free medicines on that as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How much did you pay if you did see a doctor in those days, have you any idea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well I was away a month - 'course that's late - in later years, I was away a month - what would it be, 1908 - or nine, might have been 19 
- 1909 it was. I was away a month and my bill, doctor's bill, was twelve and sixpence and he come - not every day but - quite three times a week. And it was twelve and sixpence. And I know it was twelve and sixpence 'cos I was in the National Deposit, and
 they used to pay the bill. We didn't pay it, they paid it. It - the doctor used to send this bill to the National Deposit and then they paid it. And then you got so much sick money. Besides.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you remember had much sick money you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Twelve and six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 The same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes. Every week. It all depend what you paid. I used to pay a shilling - shilling a - think it was shilling a month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What sort of date would this be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Why 1909, 1908 I were - in fact I've got books now upstairs, the - 
I paid up 'til I was - seventy. And that - and drawn it out, what I'd got in deposit, I got a little bit in deposit as - you - if you paid - regular - always had a little bit to come back. And that was put in your deposit, same as a bank. Oh I - I were in
 it 'til I was seventy. I could have been in it - I could have kept going on with it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh all right, we sometimes had a bit of a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 jangle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  with one another you know and - same as all - rest of families do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was there anyone in your family you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, don't - not particular I don't think. We all - you know - all fond of one another, we didn't - no, there were no }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 partiality}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  between any of us as I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 As a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh all - all the little lads as were running about round the streets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you play with your neighbours of the same age more than with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well we all used to play together, if they come it were all right, if they didn't they were playing with some other brothers and sisters.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 In t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
' street. 'Course it wasn't a - like street like it is now. It were only cart road, it were - all stones and sand. And - all these were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 cornfields}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
 of course, round here. There's eight farms - round here, within a radius, if you drawn a ring a mile each road, you drawn a ring a mile each road how many farms do you think's took up for building. Eight. Yes. Yes, I could name 'em. Eight farms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What were they called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well there were Farms. Home Farm. That's where - where the estate is up - just across here, bottom - beyond the school there, that field where school is, that belonged the farm. Then there was a meadow where there's a r
ow of - of flats. That used - that field used to be full of little piglets. And fowls and ducks. And then there was old Mr Bramleys, Mr Eaves, higher up on - what they call Sunrise Hill. Then there one up Lilley Fields, Beck Hill as they called it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What did you call that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Lilley Fields. Well it was like that. Well at bottom of Hilly Fields there was spring, it bubbled up - used to bubble up out - out of there and - and you could see the sand turning over when the bubbles used to come up, the sand
 was turning over. Well that spring went - were going for years and years. And I don't know what - what - whether they - culverted it or what they done to it but - I don't think it's there now. Well up that top end when you went up Thatchers Lane up to th
at top end trees used to come over and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 touch}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  one another. And Thackeray, somebody named }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 Thackeray}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
 lived up there where they built on, in a big white house up there. On the - on the left hand side there were a - a coppice, all trees and - and - full of daffodils and all them kind of things.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Who lived in the white house beyond the bingo hall here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Mrs Potter, used to be organist at Daybrook }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 church}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 . Potters, he was - he used to own some pits. He had - I don't know - I don't the names of them but several pits in - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 Lynn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  Valley Road area. Mrs Potter, she used to play the organ. I think she were quite - choir mistress or master whatever they call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh - lurky and - kicking a tin and - what they called stalky and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What's stalky?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well - well so many on the side and used to - used to - go to catch one another and then - when they catch one used to put 'em in - same as you might say put 'em in prison, used to hold 'em agen - used to stand agen a wall 'til you 
catched them all on their side and then - it was your turn to go and - go and - play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What was lurking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 That was where - where you went and hid. Used to go and hide and then they'd got to find you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What I call hide and seek?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 That's - ayes, similar, similar, aye, aye. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
- Sometimes be all - sometimes be all night and wouldn't find - one, perhaps be one we don't find at all. Aye, stalking and - stick and billet, what we called stick and billet. Some - some - some calls it stick and goose. 
Then were cricket, we used to have a bit of a cricket team, play on - you know - amateurs. Football. 'Course I'm talking about now when we were - only twelve years of age. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 We did get dirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you catch it when you were dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
No. No. No, because we always - when we went in we used to - take us coats off or whatever we'd got on and used to wash it - wash and of course it were all right then. No, they weren't as keen as - wasn't like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were you free to play with anyone you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 pleased}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14948328\charrsid6628200 ?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you belong to any youth organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have any hobbies while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, not particular, I used to draw a lot, do a lot of drawing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Can you tell me about how you learnt to draw?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When did you start being artistic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
I'd be about - well nine years, nine I should think, I used to - I used to draw all - faces and animals like - if you see in a paper you know,
 had a paper, weekly paper, used to draw - sit and draw 'em, all animals or - or - people. If they were in you know, photo's, well there wasn't - prints of 'em and - I went on from there and - and done it ever since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How did you actually start painting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Oh painting, why - I used to go to the Castle - on me own when I were a lad, it used to be a - some days it were a penny to go in and other days it was free. But I mostly wheat when it were a penny, to go in. And - I used to go round all picture g
alleries and look at 'em, study 'em and I've been to Chatsworth and - I've been all these - been to all these big - big houses round about. Different times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you ever have any lessons at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Not one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you join and painting classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No. All I done has been in me own - own house, or me mother's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How did you start oils on your own?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well one Christmas I - I went to - we went - all us family went to me aunt - me aunts and uncles like and - I - I thi
nk I had a - copper or two of me own then and - anyway I got four and sixpence. And I went and bought a box of paints, and I've got the box now. Cost me four and sixpence. And - I don't know how many colours are in - about a dozen I think. Well I started 
-
 and it was a long while before I made any progress and I kept going to these 'ere places - and if the - Boots used to show pictures then in - in their window what - artists had done, show like. And I - if there ever one in Boots in Nottingham and I were 
i
n Nottingham I always used to go and look in this window to see these pictures. And it made me have - that ambitious to - oh, you know, I - like that sort of feeling. And - I were determined. I kept going and buying stuff and - spoiling stuff and - anyway
 - as time went on I got older and began to - shape a bit. And that's how it finished up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you always prefer painting out of doors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh yes - oh yes, it's better, a lot better. Same as sketching and all. When I was in the Army - I was in the - 
there was fourteen of us in my - my section, what we call 'em - scouts section it was like - you got more - bit more privileges than what - the ordinary recruit had and - we used to go out on - before we went to France, when we were in training we used to
 
go out on reconnoitering. And - I used to do a lot of sketches - then when I was in Army. And - I were good - very good at sketching. And that - at that time - you know - and - they used to pass 'em on to the C.O. and - used to do a lot of that in our sec
tion. And of course you got from one thing to another, kept persevering and then that's how I got - I've come out. And now I don't know it all. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Is anyone else in the family good at painting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Just you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, only me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you get encouragement from your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Oh I did, yes. Yes, but - them days - you'd got to have some - either money or somebody - at back of you to get in school of art. That used to be in Waverley Street then, at that time of day. But you couldn't 
get in there without you got either money or somebody at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 back}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  - give you a push. So I never got in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was this a great disappointment to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well I should like to have got in but - I - I knew them as did get in, there was - the there was what - o
ne in Arnold as I knew 'cos he's - poor fellow's gone now - name }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 Hammonds,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
 he's got - had a lot of pictures - some pictures in the library up Arnold some time ago and his - his - sister - she sent for 'em back because they - they hadn't put 'em up. They ha
d 'em up and then took 'em down and I think they put - stowed them away somewhere and - sister complained about it. I don't know whether she got 'em back again or not. He was very good at it, well he went to school of art 'cos I know a man as used to - I 
know a man as used to take a pony down there - for 'em to - to sketch from. Live pony - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 At this stage when you were a schoolboy did you have any other hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, not particular, I used to like doing a bit of - playing - help me father in 
garden a bit and I could - I could dig. Could dig when I were a boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you keep any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
We always had - oh - well we got fowls of course but - we used to have - uncle as lived at Gainsborough and he used to - used to breed rabbits, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14948328\charrsid6628200 brown}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  rab
bits, some as wild rabbits and every year he used to bring us two of these rabbits. And we used to - be - one - well we started to - talk about it in January when he used to come - used to come in August. Oh it'll not be so many more weeks - so many more 
weeks now 'fore me uncle comes, brings us two rabbits. Well they were - of course they were only - you know - baby rabbits. Oh we used to think we were - got all the world when he used to bring us these two rabbits. And they were only sixpence a piece.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you eat them in the end or were they real pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
In the end we lost 'em 'cos - we put 'em in fowl pen and - and - and they bored a hole and - they got into the cornfield and never seen 'em no more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you get two more the next year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh we got two more next year. Brought us two every year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you collect anything as a schoolboy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You did do gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I used to do a bit of gardening to help me -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, but I've been fishing since, I've been married - a time or tow.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you go for walks as a schoolboy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Oh used to go miles. Miles. I've been to Calverton lots and lots of times. Calverton and back, Oxon. Used to go blackberrying as far as Oxon. 'Course - same as I say - them d
ays there were - there were no motor cars or very few had got bicycles and - you could go out there, you could get as many blackberries as fill a bucket.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Who did you go these walks with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well school pals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you ever go bicycling at this stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Yes. But - not - not 'til I was - I didn't have a bike not 'til I were married. I could ride one but I didn't get one because - never got the money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You did take a lot of part in sports didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes, oh aye, Forest Sports, used to - that were on City ground. That were a big thing in them - in them days. Used to be cycle races and }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 men\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
 races and - hurdle jumping and all - and all that kind of thing, it used to be - oh quite an annual affair that did. I used to like to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How old were you when you skated on the Trent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well I can't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 tell}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  you the - remember the year it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were you at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh - at school then, it was - cos it's - I don't think it's been froze - froze over same as it was then, but I can't remem
ber - can't remember the year, but I know - I - I went with - aye - went with - me older brother, me - well me half brother as was, but we never - termed him as half brother, he - used to call him his name and we classed him as us proper brother. Well he 
took me the first time I saw the Trent froze over, the canals. That year, but I can't remember the year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you skate for miles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You could if you could - that time, that winter you could skate - they could - I've heard 'em - talk about skating f
rom London Road down to - Grantham on the - Grantham canal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have skates?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Aye, little - little clog - like little clog skates there was then. 'Course they've improved on them now, they've got boots to 'em now. They were like wooden - woo
den - things as you fastened on your feet with straps and - blades were underneath the wood like - like - kind of a clog. Haven't you seen them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were they comfy or did they come off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Sometimes, they were screw - they were screw in - in the heal,
 and used to screw 'em - make a hole in your boot heel with gimlet and then used to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14948328\charrsid6628200 screw}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
 - screw 'em on - the heel and they were strap - went through hole in the wood, straight through and you used to - put it - fasten it on like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I remember skating on canals in 1939 but I've never seen a river frozen over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Aye. This were before then. This were years before then. It'd be in 18 - 18 - 1890 something, something like that. 18 - or it - it might not have been 18 - it might have been 1888 or 1889, something like that, I know I weren't very old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you go to any theatres?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Used to go to pantomime that was all. Once a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 This was a sort of ritual was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was this in Nottingham?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Theatre Royal, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 This was a real treat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh aye, it were only fourpence in gallery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you ever go to concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes. I were going to mention that later on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 This is when you were a schoolboy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 This is when I were a school - well, used to have it at Day
brook chapel, down the road here in the square. 'Course it weren't that chapel as is now, it were a - just a - a long building, all windows all down it, and then the front were like - the eaves were like that you know, straight down, a door in the middle 
a
nd it were a - and then there were a room used to go down - it were like a cellar in a sense, it - you went downhill and door at bottom of this hill, you went in it, you were like in the cellar but there were windows in and you used to have a concert ther
e
 every Saturday night. Aye, well it - it used to be the - the members - the members as belonged to the chapel - and - they used to get a concert up to get funds you know and it was a penny to go in. Tuppence for grown ups and a penny for us. And then they
 used - half time they used to - ha'penny for a cup of coffee and a ha'penny - ha'penny bun.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What sort of things did they do at the concert?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh just dialogues like and - made up themselves and - one man as used to live in Arnold used to keep - h
e used to keep that shop - I don't know which it is now but - Anthony used to keep it, years ago. Iron - ironmongers shop. Aye. Aye, it used to be - Bob Anthony used to keep it. Well the man as lived there before it were altered, it were a little - a litt
le shop - house window, went up three steps, and he used to do soldering. And he used to make kettles, tin kettles. Well he - he were a - he were the clown in all these dialogues. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you ever go to music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 There weren't - I didn't as there was any, only theatre.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 There weren't cinemas at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh no, no. Cinematograph weren't found out then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 We had about tuppence, that was all. That's about the - like - that was - tha
t tuppence - well, tuppence we used to go to the concert, it used to cost us penny to go in, penny for a cap of coffee and a ha'penny bun. And that - that was - that were all we got on - in spending money line, perhaps some aunt or uncle used to drop over
 where we met 'em and they used to perhaps drop us tuppence or threepence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you get this tuppence regularly when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh got - aye, we always had us - Saturdays ha'penny or penny or whatever it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 So did you always spend it on going to a concert?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, not always, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What other things might you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh used to buy about ha'porth of sweets we used to get quarter of sweets for - for a penny.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Everlasting strips?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Aye, all sorts of things. Bulls eyes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 Hanky-pankies, nib sticks. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 We used to get a lot for a ha'penny.
