\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  and all like there, just for one day sometimes a year. But apart from that - we - didn't - it - it weren't very often as we saw them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 The Nottingham part of the family would join you for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, well - didn't have no particular friends, they were neighbourly and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did they share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your mother have friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No. No, she had - anybody as were friendly with her she were friendly with th
em. No particular friends she didn't have. Of course she'd got a sister - two sisters in Nottingham and they used to come over occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Where did your parents see their friends? Did they go into each others houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 went}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
 to - mother went to Nottingham if she were anywhere close to her sisters she - she'd call in, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What about your neighbours, did you call in to talk to neighbours or see them in the road }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 or}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, didn't - we didn't go in not without any special occasi
on for 'em to - to - to go in or they got special occasions to come in our house. Were no - neighbourly sort of feeling like that, I mean, they didn't - make a practice of going in one }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 
another\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  house. Well we didn't anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Relatives were invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, not - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How often would relatives come?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh, perhaps once a year. Twice a year happen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Would they be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh aye. That's - that's - that's wha
t some on 'em come for. The granddad used to come for a fortnight. He were - lost his wife when she were young and - lived with his - one of his daughters. Well when we lived up there where I tell you we got that garden, the house that stands with itself,
 me granddad used to come to us - every year and stop a fortnight. And - it - well, he'd liked to have stopped }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 altogether}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
 but - hadn't go accommodation. But he always used to come for a fortnight. That were me dad's father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were your relatives invited on any particular day or occasion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No. They dropped in they dropped in, if they didn't come they didn't come that was sort of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Would you say the people who came in were your mother's side or your father's side or friends of both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well friends of both of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did neighbours ever call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Not - well I can't remember as they did without it was something special as they wanted to know or - wanted to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
No, they didn't go out to visit nobody I don't - particular, if they went out together they mostly went to Nottingham. And that were when they went to perhaps theatre, occasionally but not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 People often tell us in those days they made their own amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What did your parents do when they got together with neighbours or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh used to have - well sometimes men'd play cards and - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Just the men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Aye, mostly the men, aye, the women and children, they'd find some sort of games to amuse theirselves with, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 \lquote cos}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  there were no - there were no music then, only pianos and -and organs, there were no - radios and all them kind of things.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were you given lessons by either of your parents before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
No, but if - if we had any questions when we come home from school as we didn't understand at school we used to - ask - if they knew what it was or - how to do it, we used to ask 'em that. And they'd tell us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
He? About - I should be about three and a half. Yes, I went - went at three. I think I should have been just over three when I first went. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When you first started what time of the morning did you go and when did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well I think, if I remember - remember I think it were nine o'clock. To about twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you go in the afternoons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Straight away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 After dinner. Two o'clock 'til four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Even when you were three and a bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What kind of school was it you started at?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - board school. What they call a board school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was it mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Mixed. And there were above twenty in a class then. Aye. Sometime
s nearly best end of hundred. Aye. When I left there were - it was mixed class and there would be I should think - oh fifty. In - in my class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 Were you made to keep very, very quiet so the teacher could manage with such big numbers?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes, you had
 to keep quite then because they'd throw a book at you else a slate. Very strict you know them days. Used to - used to give you tawse, what they call tawse, it was a - a leather - strap with like - eight or nine - strips cut down like and handle and used 
to get that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What would you get that for?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well perhaps you get it - not - being - watching and - listening to what they were telling you, or if you - happened to be talking, if you were talking to anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What would they throw books and slates at you for? The same sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Aye. Oh aye. Aye they would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did they always hit the person they were aiming at?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Not always. Oh it was, it was cruel, was cruel in them days. I - there was one man, he's dead and gone now but I neve
r forgive him. He once hit me in the ear. And I used to suffer with earache in them days when were young, 'cos me dad used to get heart of onion and hot it, roast it, and then shove it in me ear and - and I remember him, he - he knocked me out of desk, an
d
 I don't - I can't remember exactly what it for perhaps I think we were laughing at somebody said something and I laughed. And that's what I got. The man's gone now but I never forgive him. And I suffered with me ears. I can see him now, coming to me and 
hitting me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your parents feel they could complain about this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 My dad - my father did go and complain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh the - a bit of a quarrel and - 'course - them days they were - they were proper brutal to you, some teachers was. They was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you think most were brutal or most weren't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Weren't many as didn't - use the - fists or the cane. Oh ayes, they were - them as goes to school now, they're - it's a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 tea party}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  for 'em. It's true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When you first started school how did you get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Used to walk, used to go to Daybrook school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How long did it take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh about quarter of an hour. Ten minutes happen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 \{ILLEGIBLE\} with you when you started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I think me mother took me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Would she have taken you for long?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - two or three weeks I suppose. Then I used to go with other children, little children. Mind you, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14948328\charrsid6628200 the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  roads were safer then than what they are now you know. There were only - there were no motor cars or anything like that, ther
e were no roughs about, there weren't many - you could walk about streets and be safe in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You came home for your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well it were - it - school was all right but - if you're a litt
le bit backward - used to get - used to get more punishment than them as - them as were - you know - more learned. There was some - learned better than others - in the - some of 'em - they couldn't learn at all. Used to shove 'em in a corner. That were yo
ur punishment, go and stand in the corner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 For not being able to learn so quickly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Aye. Used to knock - try to knock it in you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well I wasn't very fond of it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 
School were all right, it was the - it were the - teachers as you had in them days, 'cos they were - they used to - thrash you, you know if you didn't - you didn't - pay attention, they're not like - weren't like they are now. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 In them days they used to knock it into you, used to make you learn it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What did they thrash you with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well sometimes - with a cane and - sometimes with - they'd hit you on - on the head with book. Anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did they ever throw things at you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 They throwed books at you for slates. They did. They did
 at this school - I don't know about any other school. Oh it's true, aye. Yes. Oh a bit brutal you know in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were they all brutal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - there - over there some were worse than others but - and one as used to go for come from Bulwell, a man as come from Bulwell in }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 standard}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  five, he was - oh - he were brutal. He were a brute he was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were the lady teachers }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14707464\charrsid6628200 brutal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well one - one or two, there were one or two - one - one }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 Arnold}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  woman was a bit keen. Used to rap your knuckles with - with a - slate si}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 e, you know that wood on the slate. She got one of them, used to rap your knuckles with it, bruise your knuckles you know, it was dangerous. Oh they was brutal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your teachers emphasise certain things as important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No I don't know, I can't say that they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What about things like manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh you got to - you got to bow and scrape to 'em sort of thing in them days. Yes, ma'am and no sir and - like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What about things like tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 O
h you got to be tidy, used to - you'd got to be clean and all. But - mind you, the - the lads in them days had more patches on the backside than what they do today you know. And yet looked cleaner. The - mother's used to patch their clothes, and used to h
ave a white collar on, nearly all of 'em had a white collar on, and a tie, in them days. Oh aye, they were very keen on cleanliness and - in schools then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What about punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh that - you got to be there. If you didn't fall in when - in play
ground when the bell went or the whistle or whatever it was - it - if you were late they wanted to know why and - where you'd been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Would you be punished for being late?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Sometimes you did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What about ways of speaking, did they take much notice of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, no, because - all different parts of the - place like used to have a different dialect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 If you did something the teachers disapproved of would you always get physical punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Not - not always, sometimes you - it all depend what it was, if anything very serious you did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What were the other punishments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well sometimes make you stand in the corner all morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were the punishments the same for the boys as for the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 They were not quite so bad for the girls. 'Cos the - the boys were a bit }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 
rougher}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  than the girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What offences would you have been put in the corner for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well for - if - sometimes if you didn't do your sums right they'd put you in the corner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh they were keen on me going to school. But you didn't get no homework in then - when I went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your parents ask what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh yes, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did they visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, not - I
 don't - there were no parents visit the school without the - they went to see about 'em thrashing their children. And that was about the only time - and when they used to take 'em to school - if they ran away and - you know - didn't go to school and thei
r mother said - father said to her, take 'em next day. I've seen that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did the parents meet the teachers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your parents do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. Not as }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14948328\charrsid6628200 we}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh most of 'em - yes. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What were the other ones who weren't?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well a few - few like better off children went to - to the same school. But not many. Most of 'em went to college, them as got the money.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh you got favorites, yes. Oh aye, aye, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did they ever have the opposite?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were any children especially badly treated at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Not - not in particular without doing anything wrong. But they got favourites. The - the favourites were mostly the best scholars.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Groups? No, I don't think so. Don't - never - never remember any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Never saw anything like that happen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you stay at the same school all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Where did you go next?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I went to Carlton Road school in Nottingham. That's where I finished. I got -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 That's when you moved house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
That's it. Yes. I - got me - what they called the labour certificate, passed me - well - got it in seventh standard, that were passed all your standards then - you could leave then when you got your labour. 
Well I left from there, I were only - I were twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was there anything different at Carlton Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well it were - yes, there was a little bit of - more - I think a better place to be educated, the more - seemed as if they - told you more than wh
at they did at - at Daybrook school. Think they were better - better class of teacher if you know what I mean.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How did you feel about those teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well they was - they was all right, but the same - they were same as they were there, if you -
 if you run away from school or else you were late or if you - didn't behave you got the - they used to have a - a leather - strap like, it were all like tails and a handle, they used to get that we did, not - didn't use canes they didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What sort of things would you have got that for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well you get that for - if you - if sometimes if you were late above once, or - of if you'd run away from - anybody as run away from school got it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was there a special Nottingham name for that strap with tails?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Tawse I think they called it. Tawse, that's right. That's it, tawse. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did the other children there come from the same types of home as your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes, same - aye, same class of people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh they had favourites the same. Aye, it was just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Any gangs or groups there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, not as I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were there any children left out of things there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I never noticed any, but - it was a
 better class school because - half a day a week we used to go down - what they call Leanside in Nottingham and that was joinering afternoon, used to go away - joinering and - every - every lad had - got his own bench and his own set of tools and each cla
s
s used to go at different days. Well the girls, they used to go somewhere else but I don't know what they did. You left that - you left the school for the afternoon and went down to - to this Leanside and it were like a - an old building and - and - educa
tion authority took it over - lads to learn joinery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You enjoyed that did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Then they used to take us to - swimming baths once a week. Oh it was a lot better school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have organised games there or was there swimming instead?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well - no, only they used to play in school yard when it were school playtime. Got horizontal bars and all them kind of things. Yes, it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  more}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  well a lot better than what it was at Daybrook school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Would you have stayed on longer at school if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I might - yes, I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 might}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you attend any part time education afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. 'Cos I - I think I'm as good as - as some of them as is goin
g now. In fact I can write better than some of them as is going now. And I can figure better. 'Cos they can't, half of 'em their - writing you can't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 tell}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did - you get encouraged with your art at this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes, I got a certificate for drawing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh I do, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You had left school before your father died hadn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Aye, about two year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 So that didn't make any difference to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, two - about two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Many
 people divide society into different social classes or groups, in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, I don't know as I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You said some people were better off than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Aye there was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you feel they were a different sort of person?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
No. No, no, no. No, I don't think they - there were never any - partiality between the - them as was a bit better off than what them as wasn't. Because - same as I said before - all their
 mothers used to send 'em to - if they even got patches on they were all - all - had to come clean. They wouldn't have - in fact - they'd send em out to wash 'em if they come - hands were dirty or their face or - used to be very strict on that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What social group would you say you belonged to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well - let's see, there were only two groups - the rich and the middle class and then the poorest. We - weren't poorest - we - well we should be about middle class people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What sort of people belonged to the same class as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh I don't know I'm sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What sort of people belonged to the other classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well, them as had - fathers had got - better jobs and - bit of money at back of 'em you now and - used to stick their necks
 out a bit you know, some of them did. Oh aye. Well, thought they were a bit superior to what some of - poorest as went to school was. But there were - you could - you - you didn't have to sit in one place when you went in class. You could sit where you l
i
ked. So you mixed among - you all got mixed up, there were no - distinction in the - better off putting 'em all on one row and the poorest on another row, they used to mix up. You went in school all - all in a line and you - as you filled first row, secon
d row and so on, kept going on, it didn't matter whether you - rich or poor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you ever touch your cap to people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, I don't think I did. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have to show respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh yes, you - you used to show respect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How did you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well if it were madam or - or sir we used to address 'em as - yes sir, no sir, yes madam. Yes, ma'am. So on.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 The teachers would get that title as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Who else would?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Ooh - anybody as were a little bit - little bit - what you might call up the stick a bit, we used to - we used to - be a bit }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 courteous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  to them sort of folk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in that sort of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
No, I don't know as I did. Can't remember them anyway. We used to - were just ordinary - people and we used to call 'em Mr and Mrs and - that was as - as far as it used to go I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Where you lived who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well we got none there, none was very important at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When you were in Daybrook was there anyone who was considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, there was - one or two as got - good
 jobs - better - better off than us, well, plenty - there were - you could mention - mention a lot really better off than what we was and - and got plenty of money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you come into contact with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you know why they were considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well because - one - one man belonged - belonged Daybrook laundry so he was important. Another man belonged brewery. Another man kept that farm I was telling you about at - across here. They were the men as were important.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 The people who could give the jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Aye. I know - him as belonged - as - well, biggest share in the laundry that time, Same Robertson, lived on Church Drive, he - he used to - every Christmas he used to send - all the - widows and poor people a bag of co
al. Every year. Always used to bring - used to come round with a bag of coal at Christmastime. Well, a - a good many as did - as got this bag of coal you know. 'Course it were cheap then. Well it - it weren't bad - weren't a bad sort, Sammy, they used to 
call him Sammy. Weren't a bad sort. 'Course he were brother to him as belonged brewery. And did belong brewery, of course he's - they're both dead now..
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Who did the shopkeepers associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well I don't know, 'cos I - I were only a lad then and they were men and women and I - I couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you know who the clergy associated with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
I - one as used to be - as I remember being at the church first before that church was built - Master Vaughan his name was - he used to associate with - a lot with - C.G. Hugh as lived at the - where the council house is now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
He was a - a frilling manufacturer, in them days used to wear a lot of frilling, ladies did. And - they used to war it in their bonnets and all and - and he used to - visit him a - a bit I think because he - he used to like a drop of whisky.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Who did teachers associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Teachers, oh I don't know. Only knew 'em when I went to school, 'course I didn't know - know 'em personally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you know who farmers associated with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Farmers? Farmers associated with farmers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What about employers, did they just associate with each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh Sam - Sam - Sam associated with anybody as long as he - he were - he were having a drop of whisky
 because he used to - used to be one or two stand at bottom of this street and - perhaps be five or six and - jobs then you know - the money weren't very much and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 Sammy\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  see 'em standing there and he'd look at 'em and say, come in my lads, come on. He'd take 'em in and - perhaps be in all morning. And Sammy's valet used to have to take him - home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 Who did the paying, did Sammy?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 He Sam - his valet used to put it down on his cuff. Aye, they used to always call him Sam. Sammy }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 Robertson}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 , that's what they called him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What sort of people would you say went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well the - there's more - working people go to church now what they did in them days. When - Mrs Sealey used to - he used to go when it were first opened. It were all - mostly
 the - upper class as went, there wasn't - the working class most went to chapel.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I don't remember when Daybrook church was built,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What was there before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Pond. Pond. No church, only that little church as called Hall just up - u
p Church Drive. That was a church. And this church as here now, Sir Charles Sealey had that built.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did he pay for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes. Yes. And it was in 1890, when they was on it, working on it. And the bill - bells were put in about 18 - round about 1899 
and there was - oh a few years before they rang. They used to - they used to pull the - what do you call its inside, the hammers, but they didn't swing the bells, 'cos the - the - the thing wasn't set - the steeple wasn't set, two or three year before it 
were set. Aye, I went up there when the - when they'd done - finished tower, went up on a lift. About all neighbourhood went up. Aye. Aye, then they built them - Sammy - Sammy }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 Robertson}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  - not Sammy Rob}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 ert}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
son, his brother, Johnny, John they called him, used 
to call him Johnny, he built them alms houses. In memory of his son as - as died, his son were only twenty-one. He were in the Robin Hood Rifles and - had - which - the Sherwood Foresters they call them now. And - he died when he were twenty-one then he b
uilt them houses - alms houses in memory of him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do the people in the alms houses have to have worked in any of these firms,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. Not, no - no, but you've got to have somebody with some influence to get you in. You can't get in without somebody - 
back of you. Well I don't want to go in. I'm happy where I am. I don't want to go in no flats either. And I shan't go in no homes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You're an independent type aren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 A little bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh about the same I think, all about the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you think that one group felt itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh a little bit of that. Oh yes. Well - see it all 
depend what sort of - what work they done and - and - how many - perhaps some of them had got two or three children at work in - and - and perhaps another family would have a lot of children as - as going to school but - them as are going away to work, th
e
y used to - hold their pecker up a bit you know and - and think they were so - bit superior to the - to the - poorer people. But - they forgot that time when these others that had grown up you see. Aye. Well it was only - it was - well I - I'd sooner had 
that life as - as we had in this - this life, 'cos this world is not this world to me. It's different altogether to what it used to be. Yes. Yes, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 world\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  not - this world nothing like the - the world what - as I were brought up in.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What specially makes you feel the difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well I don't know I'm sure, it's - it's what you read and see and hear about and - carryings on and the - vandalism, one thing and another, murders and robberies and all that, there - there - there weren't none of that in t
hem days. Hear - perhaps hear of a murder or two but - but one - oh perhaps one every - in a year. Now it's robberies and - regular thing. There were no - professional burglars in - in my time, when I were a lad, what they call professional burglars, they
'd perhaps break into a house and steal all the silver and - and they'd go away and they wouldn't touch anything else and they wouldn't touch nobody. But now - they tie 'em up and - beside robbing 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When you were little were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh they - there was them kind of - there was them kind of rough folk. Oh aye, there was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well I don't think there was any - whether labourers or craftsmen or - there was some good labourers, good living labourers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 There wasn't much difference between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different social classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, they was all right, they were the same with everybody as far as I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 They both had the same ideas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 That's right. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No. She just - she were workin
g class, and that's - she - she - thought that. She never - she couldn't be any different to what she was, because - money were a bit tight in them days and - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you think she put herself in that class because she was thinking of her parents, her work, her house or your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well I think - she were thinking about - me - me father and - and children, us children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What do you mean, socially like? No, I don't think s
o, I don't - them sort of people used to cling together - it all depend what you was. If you got well known then you - they'd - they'd draw you in, but otherwise they wouldn't. Used to look on you then as what you was, well - whether you were a labourer o
r joiner or a fitter and - but - take it all round I don't think there were much enmity with one another at all. Not what there - same as there is now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well I know there's - there's one or two in Daybrook.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Why do you think they were described as that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well - there one or two as - would help any - body as were really down and out, there was - one or two of 'em. Now Sammy Robinson were one. He was a - you could call him a real ge
ntleman. Then there was - now who was - name of that one? There was man as used to - I can't think of his name now. But he finished up bad. He were well educated - one of the best educated men in - in the parish. But I can't remember - can't remember his 
name. It - they used to say as he could - he could }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 reckon}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
 an additional sum up or pound shilling and pence like that. But - didn't go up one row, pence and shilling and pound, he used to take the lot as - pound shilling and pence and reckon right through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Why did you feel he was a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well because he used to help people. Anybody as were down and out he'd help 'em. And the poor fellow, at - at finish - to finish him off he were down and out himself. Yes. He used to sleep out and - he wa
s a nice fellow. Cope his name was, Bill - Billy - William Cope. Used to call him Billy Cope. He was a - he was a teacher, he was a teacher in - in Park - some park of his life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What about anyone being described as a real lady?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I don't know. I 
didn't got the pleasure of meeting ladies. Not - but - there was Mrs Sealey and then Mrs - I believe Mrs Potter was a lady, in a sense, but she were very strict if you went on her field.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Why would you describe these as real ladies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well they use
d to do a lot of good in different sort of things, with different - used to have these different functions and - to help people. But - there were several in the working class as did same thing in - for their own class. Sam - Sammy Robinson, you could call
 him a - a real gentleman because he were - he were very good to the poor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Policeman? Aye. I've the had the belt round me neck and all above once.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What did you have that for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Playing round that lamp as used to be at bottom of street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were you doing any harm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well, we used to be playing at stalky. There used to be lamp at bottom of street, you called it Christmas lamp.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you know why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. It used
 to have three lights on, but not - electric lights, gas light. And we used to play round that, there were a herb round it, round the kerb, used to play }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 there}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  and - if you see the policeman coming, if we didn't - if we didn't we used to get belt round us neck. Oh used to run like mad when we saw a policeman. Fright - frightened to death.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were you always frightened of policemen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 We all was. We all was in them days. Because they would like to - they would like to get their cape, if they got their c
ape on and sling it - hit you with it, or a belt, they used to wear belts then. And if anybody - anybody was out of work he used to stand at bottom of that street which they have done for years, and if they saw a policeman coming down that hill or our roa
d they used to go - walking and get into this - this road, into kerb. Now - now they - now they stand there and knock the policeman hat off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What would the policeman do with adults, was it just children he treated roughly?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, big - grown ups. Aye. Oh aye. 'Course they stopped all that game you know, the law stopped that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When you were naughty did your mother over say, I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh scores of times. Fetch a policeman to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you take any notice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Aye, frightened to death - policeman we was when we were - well all kids were in them days. Frightened of policemen, used to run like mad.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When you were little was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Rented? What, the house do you mean? Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you see anything of the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Landlord, yes, because he - he worked across here. As man as built it was - the time as we was in it. And then - that row across - Where Miss Rose is, across the road here, not - not facing us but - down the road there across the road - t
hem belonged - Sammy Robinson brought them, he built them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What did you feel about your landlord as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh all right. Used to pay us rent and that were that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you remember feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet when your father was alive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 It were - well - we only just made 'em meet, we got no - got no money to spare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 So you can't really tell me how your mother coped?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, she used to do a bit of washing. And I was getting - I were getting about s
even shilling a week. And mother used to do a bit - she do - cleaned offices and all, used to get a bit for that, not - weren't a pound, and then she done a bit of washing, and were only me getting - taking a bit of money in, there were five of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you know if she ever got any help from the Guardians?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes. Yes. She did. She get -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How did they treat you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh - you got to be very careful. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14948328\charrsid6628200 G}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 ot to be careful. You got anything in the house as you - as you could }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 see,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  you used to get - par
t with that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How did you feel about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh it - it years 'fore I ever got over it. I don't think I ever - ever have got over it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 It was such a shock - when - 'cos me father'd got a good job, foreman. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Mind you, the money - money wasn't all that
 much, but - it were regular and he got it whether he were there or not. And - all of a sudden it happened and - I tell you, I were working across there at the same time and - I'm earning about seven shilling a week from - used to go eight in the morning 
'
til about six at night. Eight on a Saturday 'til one. That were seven shilling when I done - when I were doing that. Well when he died - only my money going in and - the firm - that were across there - let mother go and clean offices, in the mornings, dus
t 'em and - and all like that, but - the money weren't very big, I don't think it were - amounted to a pound.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you remember being hungry at that stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I do. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What about the little ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well they were - I suppose they were same 
as me but of course I were working and - I wanted a - a bit more to keep me going but - oh I've seen some hard times. I think mother had about twelve shillings from - from the - parish. And she got that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 till}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  - second - second son went to work. Me sister we
nt after me, and then, the second son, he went after her. And they kept following on, there were - perhaps three year I think between most of us. Some a bit more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was your father ill or was this something very sudden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was typhoid fever. Now if -
 if he'd - if he'd had it now - he'd have got over it. Perforated bowels. He'd have got over it 'cos they could operated on him, but they couldn't in them days. He had it twice. He had it when - just after I were born and - and them he had it in 1898, whe
n he - it killed him. He were a fortnight away, going ever so nice, sat up in bed - two days before he died. Then this - this happened. Perforated bowels.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was he in the fever hospital?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, they didn't take you in hospitals then like they do now. Oh no. At home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When you were at school did you have a part time job or any means of earning a little regular money?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14948328\charrsid6628200 Sometimes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  running errands for people, perhaps for coppers. Penny or tuppence and that was all, that was - would you call that a job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What was your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Full time job with me father, across there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What were you called? This was the four bob a week time was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When I started, yes. Yes. Well in - you were in this - where they used to stain - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14948328\charrsid6628200 curtain}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  and lace, stain it different colours rather - I used to be there to do a little odd jobs what they wanted doing you see like - errand - sort of errand.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You started as an errand boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What exactly did you have to do at this stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well - the - he - the stuff process - used to go through - different machinery, then - and somebody'd got to be at back of this machinery to - to catch it and they used to put it in baskets as it come through, do you see. So I - I - catcher, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Is that the groper term?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, it used to be a back - what they called back of the machine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 And it was eight 'til six and eight 'til one on Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Any half days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Saturday was a half day, that's all we got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
No. There was no holidays with pay then, only for the - for the - well me father used to get his, all - they were all either foremen or overlookers, that sort of thing as used to get their pay w
hen they were holidays. But the ordinary people never got no pay at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You didn't work Sundays did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. Not then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When you were paid four bob did you feel that was a fair wage or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh we used to think it was - it were - well
 it was - it was general thing all round in every trade, them - them days, there were never no - no more than four shilling or five shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you give the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 All of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I did. Had to do it an all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 So it was spent on the general housekeeping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 That's right. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 All right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - he was all right. See, the - the overlookers used to have t
he - control of you. But the manager, he - wasn't very often as he used to interview or talk to any of the ordinary workers, he used to talk to the foreman or the overlooker whatever he was - or whatever she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How did you feel about your employer and the overlookers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh all right. Was all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How did you feel about the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh I liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did having a job }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14948328\charrsid6628200 alter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  your attitude to life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No I don't think so. I were glad to be at work because it helped - me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What was your next job, was it the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
No, I went - I went down into the - bleaching department, when I was sixteen. And - I got a bit more money down there 'cos I made more time. Then - that - that part of the - of the factory, the bleaching par
t, used to have to be there at six in the morning.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 So you worked six 'til when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 'Til - sometimes nine o'clock at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 So that's where you made more money, you worked more hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Been at - we've been stoving at nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Half day on Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Half day on Sat'day and if you had a half day on Sat'day you had to go in a Sunday morning. That were how it was 'cos we - we used to be where the stuff - used to brought it, then it was all put in process - for next day, all boil
ed in big vats. It were brown when it used to come in, in natural colour, the cotton was, and it used - they used to boil it and bleach it and then dye it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You were in the bleaching side?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have a special title?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You were paid the same rate virtually but got more because you worked longer hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
No, we got a bit more down there. If we'd been making the same time as we was when we were - in the factory - I should - me wage - ordinary week it'd be about seven or 
eight shillings. Well with overtime that used to run to about - fifteen shilling a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you feel that was a fair wage or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well it - it weren't enough but we - we had to be satisfied.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You felt it was fair in comparison?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 According to other people, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 And you gave that money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh I did, aye, I had to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How did you get on with the other people you worked with there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 All right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 And the same employers and everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you like that work or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Oh I liked it. I were in it - I were in it from being about sixteen 'til I were - 'til - I finished. 'Til I retired, so - I were in it a long while.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did anything much change over all those years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well
 - I went to - firm as bought this up when - after the fire, stood - it stood empty a long while in - well, in ruins. Well - the man as belonged it he sold the business and all the lot. Well I went with 'em, and only - only eight of us went and I were one
.
 We went to - Sherwood Rise. And I were doing the same job at Sherwood Rise as I was over here. 'Cos I - followed the work you see that - I knew - I knew the work what I'd been doing here, we did it same there. So I - I followed it on. And I were there tw
enty-one year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 So you have stuck to them haven't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 So you haven't done any other job at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. My - my brother - my brother worked for 'em sixty-two year. He went - he went - went to Cindero when he was eighty. Yes. He were i
n drying - one of the drying rooms. Used to come - go through a - a drying machine and come out on rollers - and - it were always on roll like that. Well one end of - there were - women feeding it, there were clips, brass clips and it were pulled out, the
 
two - there was girl on either side of the table pulling it - just like that and then me brother used to feed it on these clips and it used to go through this - hot place - and at other end and the rollers used to fold it. Aye, backwards and forwards. Wen
t through - over the top through a roller and there were - on each end was like a crank and this used to go - backwards and forwards you see and this roller went backwards and forwards. Used to roll it. And - fold it like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Which brother was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Me older brother - me half brother really. Aye, he done sixty-two years in same trade. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Would you have preferred another type of occupation?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh I should have liked to have been a \{ILLEGIBLE\}. Aye, that were my ambition.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have any training period for any of your jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Just shown and you got on with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
That's right, used to - be shown - the job and you used to learn and - as you went along. It were like - well, it were - most of it other than what I 
done most of it clerical work like writing and figuring and all like that. Used to handle the work as it come in from off from - maker's frames. And - then we used to put it through 'til it used to be boiled and used to go through - be bleached or - or wh
at they call scoured, washed. They didn't want it white, they want it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 ecru}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
, we used to call that scouring it. That were washing it. Well they didn't - that didn't go in - in bleach vats that didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 In 1911 were you doing clerical work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 1911? I w
as - I was - I was same, doing same job, only - not a lot of clerical work but you've got to book everything, all them pieces were numbered, used to come in big bales, a piece'd be - be - about that high. Perhaps a thousand pair of curtains in one - piece
. Well then all - that'd all got numbers, and sometimes they'd have a - there was so many pairs }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 ecru}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
, so many pairs white and so many pairs cream, out of that - one piece. Well then it wanted dividing and that wanted putting through a different process. But it were all numbered and booked, and how many pairs and so on you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 So were you in charge of that section?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Aye. I did - I did it for - oh - think a good forty year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you count as a foreman or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. Just ordinary worker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you belong to a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you take part in any of its activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
No. 'Cos it - it didn't - it didn't have any activities then, 'cos boss got to know of any activities we got - sack. Oh - they were keen them bosses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you know of people getting the sack?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
No, I didn't know of anybody but that were the - I mean they are - they weren't men like they are now, they weren't so - so strong as they are now. There just - there were the unions but - not very
 - they weren't very strong. A master then'd take you - find you a job if he wanted you he'd find you a job whether you were a union man or whether you wasn't. But I - I was in the union when I was there. Four of us was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I don't know about - I couldn't - don't - answer that, I don't whether they had or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you feel that there were divisions of interest amongst workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - what sort of interest do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well some people thinking about the job and some thinking about money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Oh, they were all thinking about the job because you'd got to be careful in them days - you - you perhaps get stopped and you wouldn't do - didn't know what you got stopped for. The
y didn't want they - they didn't have you. And nobody - I mean no - they didn't come out - all come out on strike then 'cos you'd been stopped. There were none of that in them days. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Some people say that in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers, did you feel that or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I didn't feel no difference, I didn't. But there was - might - might have been in some trades might have been that distinction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 While you were working all these hours did you ever do any extra jobs to help your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
No. No. Because I'd never no time. Never no time to help. When I come - been there 'til - not so very - well it were gone - very often gone nine. I mean, mate of mine used to work with me, we've been - we'
ve been in - I tell you, stoving, in a hot stove at gone nine o'clock at night and been there at six in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What did the hot stoving mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well it's where they used to dry it, you know these nets as they have in - abroad, for mosquito's
? Well we used to do a lot of that. Used to have a lot of that. Oh thousands and thousands of bales of that. And - and it was all dried, see, used to have to dry it off. And it were all put on pegs, well - oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You had to stay 'til it was done did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Not - not 'til it was dry 'cos it used to take it all night. But stove were hot. The grates and the pipes under these grates, then these - pieces what - well perhaps some'd be fifty yards long. They were thrown over these pegs and pulled down to l
oop and then thrown over that peg and looped again and that - and son 'til you got to end. Well when they fill the stove you just shut door and - put steam on full and next morning we used to have to take 'em down. They'd all be dry, we used to take 'em d
own in cloths. They were mosquito nets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 So these hours of work were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 fairly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  usual then were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You continued to live at home after you left school didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you spend Sunday any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. I used to go to Bible class as I told you when I was - when I was in me teens. I went there for a nice few years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you take any interest in politics at this stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. I didn't. My interest }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14948328\charrsid6628200 was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  paint - drawing. And that's that - were my hobby and - the - the - when other lads - when other lads would - got to cricket matches and so forth and - I used to be at home drawing or out drawing, anywhere like
 that. Aye. We used to have some nice little - perhaps about five pals, my - about my age, we used to - we used to very often go to - Hoveringham and Hesleford and - in a pony and trap. We used to - one of us pals had got a pony and trap and Sat'day after
noons we used to - give him so much and we used to go to - perhaps Hoveringham or Hesleford or Biskiton or somewhere like that. We had some nice little outings like that. Have us tea there and - and come back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When you were working did you go out in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Didn't go out in the evening at all to tell you the truth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you make any new friends, girls or boys, at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. All - always only what were round - lived round about, that was all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you ever bring friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Sometimes, aye. Sometimes come in and play - and we used to play - perhaps play at tiddlywinks or dominoes or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have any special friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, only my special friends were my cousins. In Nottingham.
 I used to go up - use to go there at weekends and sometimes stop 'til Sunday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Would you do anything special with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, we used to go out walks then. Down Trentbridge and walk down - riverside and so on and - then back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were these boy cousins or girl cousins?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, boys. There was about my - well, just a little older than me, a month - a few month older than me but - about all the same age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your mother meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh - oh she - oh yes, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your parents expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh aye, we used to tell 'em before we went out where we were going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have to be home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What time was it, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well, when we got older it were - mostly be about half past ten time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Would there be trouble if you were late?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well, they used to grumble, but they didn't - make much comment, used to grumble about it, say, your late, it's time you were in bed and - so forth - so on like that. You didn't see many people out them in them days after half past ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You were twenty-three when you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 That's right. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 That\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  exactly right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How long had you known your wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Four year - before I were married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How did you meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I met her at factory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 She come from Upnall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you save up before getting married or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I saved up a bit, as much as I could. So did she.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your mother or her parents help you in setting up home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, mother - mother had got enough on her - on plate without -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did her family help at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Her family? No, we did it all on us own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How long were you engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Four year. Nearly four year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 So you got engaged almost as soon as you met?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
I met her when she was sixteen and I were nineteen. And we was - was always together. Mind you, when - only when she went home like, but we were - every week end we was and holidays. Oh I fond of my wife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Could you describe the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well, we didn't have no - we had a bit of a - got married from - house in first - this road next to us, first house, got married from there. We didn't - she didn't get married from her - her home, 'cos her mother were old and - she - she c
ouldn't - couldn't bother with it. She couldn't, her mother and father come but we had it from my mother's home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were you married in Daybrook church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, married at Register Office.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have any presents in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Few.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 And guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Oh - oh we had a nice little party about - about forty, something like that. All - friends and - we had a good tuck in. I think my - my missus and mother, she - she bought ham and - and - different things there to drink, bought it between
 'em. Her father bought us - something and - brothers, she'd got about five brothers, all miners. Oh aye, we had a - nice wedding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have a honeymoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. I'd got no money for honeymoons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did many people have honeymoons in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I never heard of any - as had honeymoons. It took 'em all their time to get money to get married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Where did you live after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I lived higher up street in same sort of house as this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You had a whole house to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh yes. Aye. Oh I got - I - got it before - the house before we were married, unfurnished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How many years did you live in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Not long because }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 missus\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  mother died. And then we went over there 'cos her father were on his own. And went over there, she - she begged of me to - go and - so I went and were there about two year then we come back again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 To the same house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No. Come back then to one in this row here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How long were you in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh, a long while, I couldn't tell you how many years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 'Til after 1918?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 After 1918 - let's see - oh - well we lived in these - that - this house and that house there - ever since 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Your wife would have been twenty when you married wouldn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Tw
enty-one she was - going twenty-one. Yes, in August, twenty-one in August and got married in November. And I was - I was twenty-three in October as we got married in November.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What job was your wife doing in the factory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 She worked in one of the drying rooms, she - we didn't - she didn't work there long though. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 She were only there about a year because - her mother couldn't get about, she was a - well she was a - a stoutish woman and she couldn't get about very well and - and she used to stop at h
ome and - there were five brothers going to pit and it were more than her mother could do. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 So she stopped at home and used to help her mother and see after her brothers and father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did she continue working after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No, never went to work at all. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did she do anything at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Sometimes she'd run a bit of washing - for anybody. Used to work - do a bit of lace work and all at one time. But it was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What lace work was she doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Drawing. Aye. Oh she didn
't know how to do no clipping and scalloping. Drawing threads, but it were poor paid. Matter of - few shillings and they'd be at it all week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You had five children, could you tell me their spacing, who came first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well about - about two years in between 'em all. There were - May, that's be daughter at shop, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 you\rquote ve}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
 met her haven't you? Then there was - George, he's a painter and decorator, lives at Ravenswood. He's sixty-one. He daughter's sixty-three, oldest daughter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I'll keep that quite secret.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
It don't matter if you don't. And - then there's Olive. She's two years younger than George. Then there's Fred, he's two years younger than Olive. And }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 Maud's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  two years younger than - Fred. There's only two - years difference between 'em all. Yes, it's - Funny though, a girl, lad, girl, lad, girl. Aye.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were they all born at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Yes. Aye. Oh there was no - no - maternity homes then, oh no, when they were born. They were - you used to have to save up for - the - woman as come to - the
 midwife - well there were no - they weren't registered midwives then, there were - women used to go about as did it. As learnt it and they used to - ordinary women.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 They weren't the trained midwives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have any medical help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I had Doctor Gas from Carrington. He was very - he was very good at that - there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
No. I used to help in the house, I didn't - help when it - being born and that sort of thing, I used to help at - boil kettles and whatnot and run errands and - I went - I went to Carrington to fetch Doctor Gas. And it - it were night time as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 He came for them all did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes. I come back in his - in his motor car and it was - aye, one of them - he did - one of them open things
 that - can't hardly describe it now, the old fashioned thing. And the - the wheel was here, he sat on the bonnet like that, it was all open. Frightened me to death coming home. Aye. And the lamps were paraffin lamps, oil lamps on either side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 And was there no street lighting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh none on - there were none on Mansfield Road, not 'til you got to Daybrook. Aye, about frightened me to death.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you remember how soon your wife was out of bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 A fortnight, used to - had to stop in a fortnight then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you remember when she was up for the whole day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14948328\charrsid6628200 A little}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
 at a time, oh didn't stop up all day. Only few hours and then back again and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Could you guess when she was allowed out for the whole day?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well she - about - be about nearly three week. Oh they didn't - didn't go out then in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How did you manage while she was in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well me mother seen after that. See mother lived here, down here. Well she were born, May were - that's her at shop, she were born up
 street in that house - that we left from - to go to her parents when her mother died. We hadn't - we hadn't been in it long 'fore she were born and - and - then we went to - over to Upnall and of course may went - she went with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What exactly did mother do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 My mother? Oh my mother were a bit - bit handy at that - there. Oh aye. Aye, she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did any of the neighbours help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 One - one, a woman in the same row - yes. She used to go out and - to birth - births and - well in fact she use
d to be on her own sometimes, some places. The woman up the street as used to live in the same row. Oh they all didn't have doctors then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 So you didn't have a nurse at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No. We managed, me mother did - washing and - and Mrs next door, she
 needed a bit of help she'd help and I had to help and - oh no. We used to have to pay our own doctor's bill then. Mrs Browing said he didn't do much for the children when they were under a year, though he obviously did much more later. He used to especia
l
ly play with them and nurse them under a year, but that was about all. He said he knew nothing about rough music and couldn't answer any of that question. He's obviously getting very tired and next time I shall try and gallop through the rest of the inter
view. I won't recap the first lot on tape either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How much of your earnings did you give to your wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh I used to give her the lot. Aye. Oh I couldn't keep none out of my money then
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How many rooms were there in the house you lived at most?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Same as this. One, two, three, four. Four rooms and one over the scullery. Small room like. Well there's room to - for a bed. Get a bed in. But no furniture
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You haven't got a top floor on this house have you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Only this - one - one - storey like,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were any relatives or lodgers living with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Your wife didn't have any paid help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes. Yes. Done all the washing at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your wife make or mend clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh she used to mend. She didn't make any because she - got a friend as used to make her - the girls frocks etcetera.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you do anything in that line?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Aye, mending boots. From 1919 - my missus never paid a penny for boot repairing - not 
- not up to when she died. I - I used to do 'em. Well I was skilled such as - as - I've earnt as much as twenty-five shilling a week when missus - years ago when children were little and in - doing other peoples, because in them days - there weren't the m
a
chinery as is there is now you know. It were what they call a cobbler, it were all one with - by and you know. And I - I got in - a friend of mine, he were a cobbler by profession, well he were a boot maker really, come from Leicester, and he learnt me ho
w
 to do it. And what caused me to do it, when I was in France first war my little son, youngest son of the two, he'd be about, should think he'd be about four years of age, and while I was away he - he'd wore a - a hole in middle of his sole, they were onl
y
 little button - little button up boots. And - the man as we took 'em too, used to take the cobbling to - the boot repairing to, he wouldn't do 'em because there were a little hole in. So - when I - as - as it happens I - about a fortnight after this happ
e
ned I were finished, I'd finished in the Army and - missus told me about this and so I says, well if that's it, I says, he's not any more mending of mine. I said, I'll go down to Joe Mayfield and - and ask him to sell me a piece of leather. Well I had - b
ought piece - what they call}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
a bend, it's about as - as wide as this table and about as long, a bend is. It's cut right across. It's about this width, they call that a bend, well you can get a man's sole out and a - heel, you see. So you get the sole there 
and then the heel and then another sole and then a heel. Well I - he learnt me how to do it and - and I set up on - you know, sort of on me own to mend - mend all us own boots. Well I tell you, my missus never paid a penny for boot repairing, not - not up
 'til she died. Aye.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have lessons how to do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Oh he - he learnt me. I used to go down at night. You see, and he used to learn me. In fact, he - when I got - well, he says, you - you're a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 better man}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  at it than me. So - so he - and I put
 me foot in it with - with being so clever 'cos he - he rushed two or three pair on to me every week - help him out. 'Course as I say it were all done with hand then. Used to strip the soles off with stripping, were all pulled off with hand, and then cutt
ing out, was all cut out with pattern and put - knocked on and finished. 'Course now they've got all machinery to do that, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 there\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  none - no cutting out now, it's all done with machinery. So that - that saved us a shilling or two. Aye. Well it saved us a lo
t because - there were - there were ten - ten pair of boots - used to be down there all in a row, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 children\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
, used the Sunday boots and the boots as they had on. Well when they'd gone to bed there was ten pair of boots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were clothes in those days new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What? No, no secondhand, they wouldn't wear them. No, my -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Where did you buy them from mostly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well I don't know, any shops as - used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your wife go to Nottingham?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Some - sometimes she did. Sometimes she used to buy the material and - lady in street used to make 'em for her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were new clothes for any special time like they were when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh we had Sunday - they had Sunday clothes and - and weekday clothes. Oh we all had - two lads had Sunday suits and Sunday boots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did they have them at any special time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well mostly about Master or Whitsuntide. And the girls as well - three girls. Oh used to dress 'em up for - once a year like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What sort of help with jobs in the house did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Me? Well used to fetch - coal in and chop sticks and all like that and help missus like generally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you do decorating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Missus did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Repairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh didn't do - much repairs because landlord used to - mostly do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you do any improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. Only - perhaps do a bit of painting or - a thing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What about doing cooking and washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh I used to do that - between us. Matter of fact I did all the washing up for above fourteen year, while - while missus were alive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 usual}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
 or not in your generation that the man helped?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well I don't know about me other brothers, I can't tell you, I think - think one - one brother used to help his wife. Same as I did. Becau
se in them days there - there weren't a deal of money and you - you'd all got to pull your weight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you help with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 Oh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Dress or undress them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I used to bath 'em on Friday night, most - I'm - that were - that my job on a Friday night, help to bath 'em and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you read to them or tell them stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I used to tell 'em bit of ditties you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you take them out without mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you look after them when mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 That'
s it. I used to stay - if mother went out - she only went out occasionally though on her own - same as I did, it were only something special - mostly one stopped in, we never left 'em. Never left 'em at night. Always one, either me or missus. At night.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were there any special household tasks the children helped you with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well when they got a bit older they used to wash pots you know and - break one or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did the boys do anything differently from the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What time - did the children go to bed then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh about - when they were young they used to go to bed about eight o'clock in winter, half past seven to eight o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did they put themselves to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, missus used to take 'em. Used to take 'em and tuck 'em in and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did the children share a bed or a bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
The back bedroom, there were three in, three girls, and the little room over the scullery, that was got a bed in and that was the two lads and we had the front room. 'Course when they were -
 very little - the - the youngest used to be in a cot the side of our bed. 'Til it was - grown - older like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What room was used for bathing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 We used to bath 'em on hearth. Else in copper in scullery. Copper sometimes if it was - if it was - if i
t was summer time it was copper. See, you could sit on side of copper and then - legs in and you could - they could standup and have a good - they could bath 'em as good as what they could in a bath. Aye, we used to hot the water - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14948328\charrsid6628200 get}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  the water half full then hot - get it hot enough for 'em to get in and then - let the fire go out and - and - that's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14948328\charrsid6628200 how}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  we bathed 'em in summer, then of course in winter when it were very cold we used to have - big bath on the hearth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When was bath night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Fridays. Friday night, aye. Aye, it were always Friday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you remember when the children had clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - well - they always had clean clothes at Friday night and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 
bath night}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  we didn't put no clean clothes on until they'd had a bath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Where were the main meals eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well - the dinner, we used to have it usually about one when I - I only worked across there you know, I used to be home by - from one 'til two.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Where did you have it mostly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 In kitchen here, in here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was it ever eaten in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Where did your wife cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 She used to eat a bit outside - a big thick slice of bread and marg or something of that, bread and jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have a special name for bread and butter or bread and jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, bread and jam or bread and butter or bread and lard or bread and dripping. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You didn't ever call it a jam butty or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh no, no. No. No, just bread and jam, bread and butter or bread and lard or bread and dripping or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your wife cook on a black range in here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes, when we - aye, when we had a oven in here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you ever have gas before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Gas? Oh aye, we had us gas stove, I don't know, I - early on, very early, when the first came out, the gas stoves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What time was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Why - sometimes it was bacon when we could afford it and egg and sometimes it was egg with no bacon, sometimes it was no eggs and no bacon. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 Toast and marg. Toast and butter.}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When was it eaten, what time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - why - about eight o'clock time then children used to go to school by nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you come back for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I used to come in for breakfast, half past eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 So you were all together for breakfast were you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Aye. Well - th
ey - they'd had theirs but they hadn't gone to school when I used to come home, 'cos I come home from half past eight 'til nine, well they didn't get to school - school 'til nine. So I used to see 'em before they went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you ever have anything to eat before you went off to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Me? I - used to have a cup of tea in the morning, that was all. Used to be there at six. Only - I'd only got to go across road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Your big meal was in the middle of the day was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Dinner, yes, what we called dinner, lunch as some people call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What sort of things did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh used to have - sometimes she'd buy a - a breast of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 mutton}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 , and some }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 sheep\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
 liver, well - we used to - she could - stuff that in the oven, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 frizzle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  it and - put s
tuffing in it between you know and make a - used to make a nice dinner. Then you - perhaps we should have a rabbit one day. Well they were only ninepence, nine - well best were only shilling. Ninepence and a shilling then for - that used to make all - us 
a good dinner. Sometimes'd have - she'd buy a pigs hock and make pea soup.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have anything different on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh - no, we did have egg and bacon always, or egg - or bacon and tomatoes always on a Sunday and we always had a piece of beef 
or mutton. Well a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 piece}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
 you know, of course you get a - biggish piece then for about three shilling. It is. Oh we - when I were first - when we were first married for eighteenpence you used to get a piece of meat }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 
very}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  near as big as a brick - for eighteenp
ence. Bacon at fourpence a pound, lard at fourpence a pound, sugar at tuppence. Matches were threeha'pence a dozen boxes, not dozen matches, boxes. Threeha'pence a dozen boxes. Candles were a farthing. Of course you hadn't got the money. Aye. You could ge
t two penn'orth of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 sheep\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
 liver then. And get it - nice big lot - for - for tuppence. And then sometimes she'd have a - what they call pieces fry but they don't make it now. Used to be bit of kidney, bit of liver, bit of smelts, bit of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 sweetbread}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 , and - and a bit of - all different things like that, well then if you got - pound of that and - two }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10500346\charrsid6628200 penn'orth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  of - of liver, you got a - a potful. And onion in it. And that - that didn't cost two shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What was the next meal of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well tea wer
e next meal, sometimes have a bit of fish or - perhaps a - if we were bit flush we should have a tin of - little tin of salmon. 'Cos salmon was only sixpence a tin then. Bit tin, long tin. Aye, big as that. I can remember when lobster were as cheap as sal
mon. Yes. Oh you get a big tin for sixpence. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 Now}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  you got to give three shilling for a little tin - no more than what one can eat

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 bake}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
 bread at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Missus sometimes made - made it. Not regularly, no. 'Cos we used to - we got a good bake
r and it - it were bread as I used to like 'cos it were - what you - I call close baked, it weren't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 spongey}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
 and weren't puffy, it were solid you know, when you'd had a slice of that you - it was better than three slice of this. 'Cos it was solid and - close baked I used to call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you make jam or pickles at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Missus used to pickle onions but she - unfortunately though one day I - I dug me - tulip bulbs up and I put 'em in the pantry there in a - in a bag and - missus }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 pickled}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  - were pickl
ing 'em. Aye. Aye, she'd done it - she'd done one jarful, when I come in and I saw on - one a mangle table there and I looked and - I says, how - what - what's these? She says, then onions. I got some onions in there, but she got wrong bag. Aye. I says, w
h
at - I says, what have you done, couldn't you smell? I says, you - you've done my tulips. Skinned all my tulips. Well - 'course she - she didn't - she - she had to - she couldn't tell, she thought they were onions. I used to grow shallots then, and - got 
s
ome in there in a bag and - and it were my fault really, never ought to have put the tulip bulbs in there in a bag, ought to put 'em somewhere else, and she - picked the first bag up and thinking they were - onions you know and then - of course she skinne
d 'em and she - she hadn't got vinegar to 'em thought, good job, she hadn't spoiled her vinegar. But she spoilt all my tulips.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did she make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Occasionally, aye. When fruit were cheap like, well it was cheap then I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did she make wine or beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No. We didn't make no - bother with no wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did she make any medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. We only used to have the old fashioned brimstone and treacle and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 
senna pods}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  and - and - rue.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What did you have rue for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Make you eat. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you grow your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Aye. And wormwood. Used to grow that an all. Oh aye, we used to - sometimes when they - used to break out a bit you know with cold - the old brimstone and treacle pot used to come out and all had to have a - a - have a lick of that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was it as horrid as }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14948328\charrsid6628200 I}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  understand it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your wife bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Not very often. No, no vegetables because they were - they were so cheap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What did you grow in the garden in the fruit and vegetable line?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well I didn't grow no fruit only blackcurrants, and I grow - grew - and - and then I - I used to force a lot of rhubarb. In fact I - I've pulled rhubarb - how many years ago is it now, see - some - well say - it wouldn't be
 above ten years ago, I went to garden and pulled force rhubarb about thirty pound odd - sticks as high as that. Used to put some - apple barrels over them, forced it. I had fourteen roots of rhubarb and I had about - twenty or thirty red currant trees. I
 used to bring bucketfuls of blackcurrants down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What about other vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Oh 'tatoes and - peas, kidney beans, cabbage. Parsnips, but I couldn't grow carrots. No, oh - oh it weren't my fault, it was land. Couldn't grow carrots. Could grow parsnips a foot long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Vegetables were bought as well, you were saying they were cheap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Cheap, aye, oh yes. Used to buy 'tatoes with peck then, not - not with pound, peck. When -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Tinned? I
 don't - there weren't many, only about - I think there were them Bartlett pears that - running at that time of day, and apricots, and I think that - and peaches and - I think that were about the only fruit there was. And tomatoes, I don't know whether yo
u call them a fruit or not. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Tinned tomatoes were quite sort of widespread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh they was, aye, most people had them. Specially on Sunday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you keep any livestock for the family, hens or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Me I had a few fowls when I lived in other yard. About - dozen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Why looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well I did as a rule, missus used to do if I wasn't about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Meat? Every day. Aye. One sort or another. Oh were never without meat for us dinner. Without it were fish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Tinned meat ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Tinned meat? No. There were only corned beef then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was any extra meat ever obtained from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Sometimes it - somebody'd bring a rabbit round, some poachers'd come round with a 
rabbit, hit cheaper than them you bought out of shop but not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you ever notice if your wife ever had to go short so that you and the children could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - we both went short, me and missus and all. I know my missus did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you need to have larger helpings of food because of your work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, no, no, only just normal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were the children allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - just - well they were only little, they used to talk to one another, we didn't - chastise them, not without they got unruly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Could they choose what they wanted to eat from what was cooked or have a little bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 They used to have what - what we had, and they used to have a bit of - vegetables and meat and s
o on, but they - they were never - choosy about what they wouldn't have, they used to have to - it were either that or going without.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What would your attitude have been if some food was left uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 They didn't very often leave any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you know what would have happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
No, I don't know, if they couldn't eat it, they weren't very well perhaps, might leave it sometimes but - as a rule they used to - eat it all up. And the missus used to make a rice pudding a time or two and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 Yorkshire}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  pudding and - oh they were fed well.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did they wait until things on the table were offered to them or could they ask for things like salt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh they used to - ask - pass salt or pass the - whatever they wanted like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Could they ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Aye. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did they have to hold their knife and fork in a certain way or sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, there were no - no restriction on - we used to - tell 'em to which hand to put the fork in and - which hand to
 put the knife in but - they mostly picked it up all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Could they bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, we didn't have no toys, not while we're eating.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When did members of the family leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well mostly when they'd all 
done, mostly used to be about all - done together. I mean, perhaps missus be finished first and then we should wait 'til they'd done and then - they'd all get up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 If you hadn't finished could the children go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 They could if they were going anywhere, if they're going out or going to school or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did all the family have a special place to sit at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Aye, they always sit in one place, same place every time. Oh there'd be a row on if one got in the wrong - if one sat
 in - another's place, always had your own place. Or else - start grumbling at one another a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Who served the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Missus.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 In what order?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I used to cut meat and missus used to serve vegetables and - and then when I'd cut the meat they - she used - she used to - put it out.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were you served in a special order?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was it oldest first or youngest first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. I don't know, I - I don't know, I think she used to - see children - give them theirs first - on account of going to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How did you cope with children too young to feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Missus used to feed them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Where did they sit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 She - used to sit in high chair. And she used to feed 'em, keep giving 'em bits you know on a spoon and - that's how we used to go on.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When your children were young did you feel there was a right way and a wrong way of bringing up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh I did, I knowed the right way, used to - we used to bring 'em up what we thought were the right way anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were there any special things you felt were important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 don\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  think so. They used to go to school and Sunday school and - they all went to Sunday school when they were little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you and your wife have the same ideas about bringing up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well, missus used to have the - mostly have the running of the - of bringing 'em as regards to behaviour and all like that, but in - if they didn't behave and she'd say, well I shall tell your dad when he comes, well they knew what that meant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What did that mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well - if they were big enough they used to get a spank or two. 'Course you couldn't - you couldn't do it to youngest but - but with the oldest, if they didn't behave they used to get - one or two - oh I was a bit strict,
 my missus was particular, on that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you spa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14948328\charrsid6628200 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
k them with anything special, you mentioned a ruler?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No I didn't - no - it mostly - with - with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14948328\charrsid6628200 my hand.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  And that didn't - that didn't happen very often. Not very often it didn't. I'd only got to put me - me - put me thumb up like that and - silent - silence. Aye. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was there anyone you used to talk to if you were worried about the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No, I - don't think so, I don't - I think all us worry we kept to ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was your mother alive when your children were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How often did you see her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Me mother? Used see her every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you ask her advice in bringing up the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh she used to - tell us different things like, how - how she brought us up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you and she have the same ideas on this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What about your mother-in-law?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Mother-in-law, I never see me mother-in-law, because she died when - the oldest was - about a year old. She died in - she died in abo
ut 1009 I think it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Could you tell me some of the things you felt you ought to do for your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
I should have liked to have done a lot if I'd had the money, but it - I couldn't do it here only - only bring 'em up right and feed 'em well and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14948328\charrsid6628200 raise}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  them as best I could and - I couldn't do no more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You felt discipline was important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What about things like affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh - oh the - we were all close to one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you feel safety was important?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Sa
fety? I used to warn 'em about when they were out if a - you know, if - you know what lads was - climbing and all that sort of thing, I used to warn 'em about that. In }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14948328\charrsid6628200 particular}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you want them to share their worries with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh used to com
e home and - if there anything - anybody'd said anything to 'em like if they'd been - bit naughty or anybody'd spoke to 'em about it you know, they used to come home and tell us and of course I used to - reprimand them a bit. If they knew that they were d
oing wrong, I used to tell 'em they were doing wrong. I didn't side with them if I knew they were - they'd done something they didn't ought to have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was it ever the other way on and you felt they were unfairly treated?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh aye, I used to side up with them if I thought as somebody'd got on to 'em as - you know, as - no need.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How did you want them to behave towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well I - I don't know, they used to call mother and of course they always called me dad, didn't call me father. Was 
always dad and - if they wanted to know anything they used to come to dad and ask him - me opinion and what they should do or what they shouldn't do and - of course I used to try and put 'em on the right road. You got a bit of a job on you know with five.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When your children were young did you both ever manage to leave them so you could go out together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. Never. Never in us married life have we ever gone out and left - left 'em -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Even with a granny or anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 With nobody. Nobody. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you let your children join in when grown ups were talking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
No. Because it - they didn't - they wouldn't do. My - my oldest lad as - as is now, if you took him out and took him in anyone, went in a - we went in anybody's house as we knew 
he'd sit on a chair, we'll say as might be there, and he'd never shift. And he'd never speak. That's how they were - that's how they were brought up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What did you bring them up to consider important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - like to behave theirself and not to be cheeky to - to their elders and - keep out of mischief.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you tell them they should hit back or not if another child hurt them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I tell them to hit back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Girls as well as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - it weren't very often girls were in
 any - no sort of trouble like that. Most of the lads because - lads were a bit rougher you know and - used to mix with other lads the same age and - there was always a bit of a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were there any other children you discouraged your children from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, I don't think so, I don't know - can't remember any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 If your children did something you disapproved of what would happen, it was mostly your wife dealing with this was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 In that sort of thing, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What would she start with doing then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well - well she - she'd perhaps ask me what - she should do and if I sided with children she'd - she'd - give way to children, but if I said, well they - ought to reprimand 'em about it or stop 'em or - let 'em go or whatever it was s
he then - she - she'd do what I wanted to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How did she punish them in the first place, she'd tick them off would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes, she used to tell 'em off sort of thing. But it weren't very often she used to spank them or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How often would they have been spanked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh not very often, 'cos it - the - they daren't - they daren't do it when we told 'em not to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How did you deal with them in the first instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was it always the spanking stage by the time it got to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
No. No. It didn't - It didn't very often get to that because, same as I've told you, if I was to put me thumb up like that they'd know what }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  meant. I've been at - when they've been - sometimes when the girls have been }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 upstairs in bed,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
 they used to be - sleep together and - they're a bit - you know, have a bit of fun or something of that sort of thing when they got to bed and - and grumbling who'd got most room in bed and - they'd start doing a bit of arguing, well I - if I sho
uted upstairs to 'em it were - it were soon silence.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Do you remember any particular occasion when you punished them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Could you tell me about the time when you had a real good punishing when you played truant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh won I ra
n away from school? Oh I were only a lad, I don't know how I should be then. I should be about - I think about ten, nine or ten, me and - a lad as I used to go }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 out}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  with, we didn't go to school one day and we went on Lane and - we never went home to dinner 
and - 'course his - his mother come to - to my mother to see if I - she'd seen him and she said, my lad's out and all, so they guessed as we're both together and - we - we had it - we fed on blackberries all day, and went - when we got teatime, when we go
t in at teatime we were - both of us hungry. I got a good hiding, I don't know what he got, I - I got good hiding and sent to bed. And I never come out to next morning, I know - know - I didn't have no tea, no - no food. That were my punishment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What form did the good hiding take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh me dad - me dad used his hand - on me bottom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No slipper or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh no. No, not as bad as that. A punishment - punishment was going to bed and no - no \{ILLEGIBLE\}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Would you say your children rece
ived the ideas of how to behave from both of you or did one of you play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
No. If - if missus thought as it would be - be on their - she used to say, I shall tell your dad, and then she used to tell me and then I us
ed to - reprimand 'em. And they knew what that was. They - they didn't go as far as to want a good hiding because - I'd only got to speak to 'em, and specially at table, they never spoke at table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When your children had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Oh used to have a little bit of a fuddle between 'em. Perhaps bring a - one or two of their pals in that they used to play, when they was little like. Used to have a little bit of a fuddle for 'em.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What is a fuddle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Why - tea and buns, you know, kiddles like sweet stuff, tarts and all like cake and - ginger beer and they used to play games and - then about - getting on for perhaps seven or eight o'clock we - we used to - bundle 'em all off. And ours - ours used to - 
get ready for bed then. Oh we used to have a little bit of a - tea party for 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did they have many friends in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh perhaps four or five, they used to go to school with and play with outside }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 like}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did they receive presents on their birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Not many. Not many presents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 If they had presents would they be frivolous things or would they be clothes or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 Well used to - sometimes buy 'em clothes or - their aunts or uncles or - whoever, but mostly come from us own relation
s, they'd buy 'em perhaps a new frock, or -new - a new pinafore or - they wear - wore pinafores then you know girls did, and - and under - underclothes or lads'd perhaps get new shirt or something like that.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did anything special happen with the family on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh - oh aye, we used to have a proper do on Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well used to have aunts and uncles and - cousins come and - perhaps come to our house for one day and two - sometimes two days, they've come and stopp
ed all night. We've made room for 'em somehow, some - gone to bed and all the children used to get into bed, as many as we could in one bed. Oh aye. We used to always have a Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was there anything special to eat at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Aye. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Anything you remember you always had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well sometimes - sometimes had a leg pork or - or sometimes we'd have a - a little turkey. Or - or two cockerels. A rabbit. All like that.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did the children get presents at Christmas then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh always had presents. And when they hung their stocking up. Aye, they always had something in their stocking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was it anything special that had to go in the stockings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 A new penny and orange and - a toy, some kind of a toy or a game, something like that
. Oh I - I've got things now in the house as - as they had in their stocking when they were young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did any of you sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 We used to - the old - old 'uns used to have a bit of a sing-song and different things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you play any games with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Aye, blind man's buff was - all them sort of things. Oh used to have a proper merry - Christmas. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you and your wife join in the games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh we all played together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were there any books in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Books? Not 'til I - not 'til I bought them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What stage did you buy those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh had them - some time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you get newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I used to have the Post every night. Sundays paper at - one paper on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you get magazines at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
No. Didn't bother with magazines, well there weren't many magazines in them day, not like there is now, there - there's more magazines now than there is ordinary daily papers.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you belong to the library?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, there weren't no libraries then, wasn't a library. No, no library then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you read aloud to each other or to the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh used to read - when they used to have a story book we used to - with pictures in, we used 
to read to 'em. That learnt 'em you know a lot, before they went to school. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were the children taken out visiting to neighbours, friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Only to their aunts or uncles or - or their grandma.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were they taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you ever take the children out without your wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes, did occasionally, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What did you do on Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well, we used to walk to Langley else Oxon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Even with the little ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes. And we used to put the litt
le one in a chair, pushchair, them as could walk used to walk. We used to go up - top of Mapley and all - then down all them footpaths as we knew then, I don't know whether they're there now -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 The footpaths are labeled now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Aye. Oh yes, yes, yes
. Aye, well we used to go - we used to go to perhaps - through Eppistone and work us road round and I remember one - one Whitsuntide, we - we went to - to Calverton, we've been all round Eppistone and we - about teatime when we got to Calverton, coming - 
w
e were coming back then, on the road back. Well, at Calverton there was a - a - a young man as worked across there at the time, when I did, and he lived there with his mother, he weren't married, he were single then, lived there with his mother and he kep
t a lot of fowls. Lived in a cottage, one - you know -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14948328\charrsid6628200  them}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
 old fashioned cottages, and he kept a lot of fowls and he'd got orchard at back of the house with these - these fowls used to run about. And - all kiddies was tired out you know with walking, well 
we were tired, and - we went in the orchard and - 'course we'd go us own tea, we took us own tea and - but anyway his mother come out to us and - and she mashed - she mashed a big teapotful of tea, I think there was - there was my five, and three - of - a
 
friend of mine as I worked with and his wife, and he'd got three, three lads. That were five - that were eight children and four - grown ups. And we went in this orchard and - the old lady - mother of this - fellow as worked across here, she went and - ma
s
hed tea for us and she boiled - boiled about a dozen eggs, and - brought 'em out to us. And - we had this - these eggs in the - the orchard and this tea and - and we stopped there and they'd got a swing and the kiddies played on swing and - oh we had a ri
g
ht day that day. So we come up - I don't know whether you'd been up - Georges Hill, do you know where I mean? Well we come that way back. And - he said, now, he said, this fellow - he said, now when you get to top of Georges Hill, he says, wait 'til I com
e
 to you. And - he said, I'll come to you. Well we got to top of the - the hill and - all at once we heard a bang. And - 'course we didn't know what it was. Then we heard another bang. About a quarter of an after - quarter of an hour after we heard this ba
n
g he come out of - from some trees with two rabbits. And he gave - aye, and he gave us a rabbit a piece. Been - been and shot 'em. So it were - our day that was. That were one Whit Monday. And - we were coming through Calverton, there were an old fellow -
 
oh I should think he'd be - perhaps eighty, and all - this - our children altogether were - three of his and five of mine - and this old man, he patted them on the head like that, he said, nice children. Nice children. And my - we often used to - since th
ey've been grown up our children - they've often said, nice children, nice children. Aye, oh we had - we had a good day that day.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Not that - not - not when the children was - not 'til they grown up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Could you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days, were they any different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
No, only - sometimes I should go to a football match, there used to be in a field across back of factory here and - that were all, I never went away from home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Could you tell me how you spent Sundays in those days, I know your children had different clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Sunday? They all went to school and - sometimes I had to go to work of Sunday morning, very often. Often Sunday morning, yes, 'til dinner.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you at that stage think it was wrong to work or enjoy yourself on Sunday or did you think it didn't matter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well I didn't enjoy myself a deal on a - same as I did in a weekday but - I used to go to - then when I had chance to go because it was a bit extra money. And that were the reason I used to go, it weren't because I wanted to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you allow the children to play games on a Sunday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14948328\charrsid6628200 No, didn\rquote t \endash  not games.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6628200  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14948328\charrsid6628200 Sunday was Sunday and that was it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you yourself attend a place of worship or - not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Me? I used to go to Bible class bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Went church at night. No. When I've been to work at Sunday morning I'd had enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your wife attend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No, she was same as me, she was tired after she'd seen after us all. No, it was hard going then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was grace said at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Who said it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Missus used to - say a word or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were your children taught to say prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh they always said their prayers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Who taught them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Missus used to tell 'em. Oh they all said their prayers before they went to bed, when they was young. Of course when they got older they - we don't know what they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 At that stage did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No, I didn't. And I - I'm not very interested in 'em now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When you and your wife were not doing your work how did you spend your time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - reading, mostly reading. I used to read a lot then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You said you never went out together, when you went out separately where were you going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Why somewhere perhaps of an errand, that were all. Didn't - no - didn't go out to - go out to enjoy ourself or anything like this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Your wife never did either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What time did you get home from work in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Why sometimes it were half past nine at night. Been later than that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 So you didn't go to pubs or clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No, I never got club - had got club money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you belong to any savings clubs then or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 A boot club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 A sick club at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I were in a sick club, National Deposit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Funeral clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, we used to pay - missus used to pay insurance. But she stopped that when she got older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Neither of you took part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Not when I was older I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you ever go to any theatres or concerts or music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes, we'd a theatre - when we got older we used to go to theatre occasionally when there were anything on special. A
nd we used to go - sometimes go to the Empire, of course that's pulled down now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 When the children were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14948328\charrsid6628200 young}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  did you ever do this?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I was painting then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have much time those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Not - not much, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Pets? No. I had nothing - no - nothing live, only what you could eat, and that were fowls. Or - half a dozen - I used to keep few ducks sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your wife have any hobbies like you had the painting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
No. She used to do a bit of crocheting and - bit of - plenty of knitting, she'd do some knitting, that were her - most she used to do in - in that line - aye, hobbies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your wife ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Not without me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did anyone outside the home help you, neighbours or friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Oh neighbours were all right, they didn't help us in - in - in - work like or anything like that. But if there was any time - perhaps missus weren't very well or - they'd perhaps come in to a
sk, they'd say, do you want a bit of washing doing, or can I do you a bit of washing or can I bring you anything up the street or - in the food line or anything like that, but - that was all. The neighbours were better neighbours then than what they are n
ow. Oh the neighbours, yes. Better neighbours - well I think so, I don't think - this world's not same as it was when I were younger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Why do you think people are not such good neighbours now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Why because I think they all - I think they're all self. That's what I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You saw quite a bit of your relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How much did you see of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - perhaps - sometimes perhaps a month or something like that. 'Course they - all our relatives were in Nottingham.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 So you saw them in your house or in their house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 That's right. This - perhaps me aunt'd come, mother's sister'd come over and - like that and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you have any friends who weren't relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Any friends? No, never had no particular fr
iends, always used to - speak to people like, neighbourly sort of thing but - we never - we never went out - never went out with no friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were friends ever invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Not without we wanted 'em for anything special like, wanted to 
ask 'em anything or to do anything - when either of us were not very well or anything like that, or children weren't very well, used to perhaps ask 'em to come in just to ask 'em their opinions, 'cos you know what children are, they had all sorts of compl
aints when they're young, measles and - chickenpox and all like that, well if my missus were a little bit doubtful she'd perhaps ask - ask the neighbour to come in and have a look at 'em and - see what they thought and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were they ever invited in on particular days or occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. Never - never had anybody in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did they ever call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did your wife ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No. No, we - we never bothered with - never bother
ed about neighbouring. No cups of tea in three o'clock in afternoon, none of that. No. Didn't have none of that
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 People often tell us in those days they made their own amusements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Can you tell me more about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, only I 
think what - what I've already told you. That's it, and tea - birthday parties or - anything - if any - aunts or uncles used to come we used to perhaps have a bit of something special at teatime or like that but - that - well you couldn't afford it in the
m days, I mean it - you just got enough if - if you'd had another pound a week, if everybody - working man in them days had got another pound a week he'd been all right. We were just that short.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Before the end of the war when you were doing overtime, Sundays as well, what was the most you ever earned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 About twenty-seven and sixpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 For a whole week and overtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 That's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Makes you think doesn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 It does. Makes you think as - what rogues there was, to employ you for th
at money Don't it? When - when you - when you see what they're getting now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 This never made you interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Because you felt it was unfair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 It was unfair. You - you were only - you were only slaves. That's all. Well yo
u - you've only got to go that lace drawing - job. Fancy drawing about a dozen lengths of that for a farthing. Well it was. It was same - same as seaming. I don't know how many dozen they had to do for - for - I don't know how much they got, but very litt
le. Only a few coppers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What about when you were dealing with the trades unions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Oh they - they hadn't got not power then like they have now. No. If you got a raise in them days, if you got a raise it were only a - perhaps get a ha'penny an hour.
 That were all. You didn't get no pounds. Same as they do now, ask for five pound raise - rise and - ten pound, seven as they are doing now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you feel bitter about it at the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes. I did. I did. 'Cos it was not - it was - slavery, that's all it was. 'Cos-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were some employers better than others or were they much of a muchness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - well I don't know because I only worked - I only worked for one. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 You must have felt they weren't too bad to have worked there all those years?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - I mean you - you - you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 daren\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 ' say anything, if you did you - would soon tell you they didn't want you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 So you really did feel it was a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes, I did struggle. I had a struggle. I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Were you ever ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Never out of work, I've been ill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What happened then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I used to get me sick pay, that were all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What would that have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Twelve and six. And they used to pay doctor's bill. Out of National Deposit. They do
n't do it like that though now. Used to get my twelve and six per week and they'd pay the doctor's bill. Well then they altered that. When the insurance come out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 How often were you ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well I think me married life I think -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I mean up 'til 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh up to 1918 I think I only remember being ill once.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was it for long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 That must have been difficult?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 It was. I only got twelve and six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did friends and relatives help over these sticky times or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 The
m as - were a bit better off than I was myself might have - given missus half a crown, something like that. Perhaps bring us - bring us something in - in food line.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you feel families helped each other like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well they didn't - they did 
more than they do now, as far as I know, but - same as I've said before - neighbours was - were better to one another then than what they are now. Well, what I've experienced.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Had you known your neighbours for years and years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Yes, some of them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you ever get help from the Guardians or the Parish or a charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 I didn't. Mother did when I was - before I were married, mother used to get - a bit from the parish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Rented? Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 No, only his agent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 So you can't really say what you felt about the landlord as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - they weren't - the rents weren't very high in them days, this - this were only four and threepence a week in them days,
 that you're talking about now. Only four and threepence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What would the rates be, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
Well the rates went in it with that. I don't know, wouldn't be a deal. Wouldn't be a deal less the poor - poor rent - property owner wouldn't hav
e got a deal out of it if he had to pay a deal rates out of four and threepence would he. Wouldn't be a deal, very - well I mean, they were - the - the place wasn't like it is now, it were only country village. They didn't have - they didn't have }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 dustbin men}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  then, there were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 dustbin men}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 
 then, there were no roadsweepers and all like that. All as there was sweeping the roads was a - horse and a - and a - machine with a big long brush and it used to - sweep all the - all the roads up. There were no tarmac, wer
en't tarmac then, all - made of stones and soil, roads was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Was there regular flooding down Front Street and the end of Cross Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Years ago? Oh aye, used to go and skate on that part where - Adam Caves - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 
garage}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  is. Aye. That field it were - used to call that meadow. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1186924\charrsid6628200 
Well from - from the - chemist shop, whatsisname, Carlson, Causon or whatever his name is, from there - down to - Anrott Hill Wall there were wall - brick wall six foot high, round there, all down there, well on other side it were
 what we called meadow and it were low like lay low. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well every time it rained - from that pond in park used to overflow }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14948328\charrsid6628200 
its banks}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200  and it used to run into this meadow. And we used to go and skate on when it were - we'd bad winter.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What sort of skates did you have in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Oh - we used to - most of 'em clog skates. Oh if you got a pair of what they called skeleton skates you were well off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4284859 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 What were clog skates like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9333648 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5733652\charrsid6628200 Well - piece of wood like a - about like this slipper, like tha
t, have a screw in heel and a - a nick there and there and that went right through. Used to put a strap through. Over there like that, fasten it round here and buckle it up, and used to put - you used to get this skate, there were screw in here. Used to g
et a gimlet and - make a hole in your heel - your shoe and - screw it on like that. Then when it were tight you used to - put your - strap through there and put it round your ankle.
